1
00:01:00,350 --> 00:01:03,560
I knew Harvey Dent.

2
00:01:04,310 --> 00:01:05,890
I was his friend.

3
00:01:08,100 --> 00:01:11,780
And it will be a very long time before

4
00:01:11,780 --> 00:01:14,230
someone inspires us the way he did.

5
00:01:16,490 --> 00:01:18,570
I believed in Harvey Dent.

6
00:01:37,590 --> 00:01:40,430
Dr. Pavel, I'm CIA.

7
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:41,640
He wasn't alone.

8
00:01:41,810 --> 00:01:45,850
- Uh, you don't get to bring friends.
- They are not my friends.

9
00:01:46,020 --> 00:01:48,020
Don't worry, no charge for them.

10
00:01:48,270 --> 00:01:49,650
And why would I want them?

11
00:01:49,650 --> 00:01:51,980
They were trying to grab your prize.

12
00:01:52,230 --> 00:01:53,820
They work for the mercenary.

13
00:01:54,360 --> 00:01:55,860
The masked man.

14
00:01:56,530 --> 00:01:58,900
- Bane?
- Aye.

15
00:01:59,610 --> 00:02:01,660
Get them onboard. I'll call it in.

16
00:02:10,250 --> 00:02:12,580
The flight plan I just
filed with the agency

17
00:02:12,750 --> 00:02:16,960
lists me, my men, Dr. Pavel here

18
00:02:17,130 --> 00:02:19,340
but only one of you!

19
00:02:21,930 --> 00:02:26,640
First one to talk gets
to stay on my aircraft!

20
00:02:33,570 --> 00:02:37,230
Who paid you to grab Dr. Pavel?

21
00:02:42,030 --> 00:02:44,370
He didn't fly so good!

22
00:02:44,530 --> 00:02:46,540
Who wants to try next?

23
00:02:47,500 --> 00:02:49,120
Tell me about Bane!

24
00:02:49,290 --> 00:02:50,790
Why does he wear the mask?

25
00:02:53,590 --> 00:02:55,960
A lot of loyalty for a hired gun!

26
00:02:56,130 --> 00:02:59,800
Well, perhaps he's wondering
why someone would shoot a man

27
00:02:59,970 --> 00:03:03,090
before throwing him out of a plane.

28
00:03:07,060 --> 00:03:08,770
At least you can talk.

29
00:03:08,930 --> 00:03:10,060
Who are you?

30
00:03:10,230 --> 00:03:12,690
It doesn't matter who we are.

31
00:03:13,150 --> 00:03:15,310
What matters is our plan.

32
00:03:21,650 --> 00:03:25,070
No one cared who I was
till I put on the mask.

33
00:03:26,660 --> 00:03:28,660
If I pull that off, will you die?

34
00:03:28,830 --> 00:03:31,000
It would be extremely painful.

35
00:03:31,290 --> 00:03:32,330
You're a big guy.

36
00:03:32,500 --> 00:03:33,710
For you.

37
00:03:37,630 --> 00:03:39,880
Was getting caught part of your plan?

38
00:03:40,170 --> 00:03:41,550
Of course.

39
00:03:46,510 --> 00:03:50,020
Dr. Pavel refused our
offer in favor of yours.

40
00:03:50,180 --> 00:03:52,280
We had to find out what he told you...

41
00:03:52,290 --> 00:03:53,690
Nothing. I said nothing.

42
00:04:07,080 --> 00:04:10,620
Well, congratulations,
you got yourself caught!

43
00:04:10,790 --> 00:04:14,210
- Sir?
- Now what's the next step of your master plan?

44
00:04:15,080 --> 00:04:16,790
Crashing this plane

45
00:04:22,130 --> 00:04:23,630
with no survivors.

46
00:04:46,990 --> 00:04:48,030
Mayday, Mayday!

47
00:05:34,290 --> 00:05:37,460
Aah! What you doing to me? Let me out!

48
00:05:40,500 --> 00:05:41,790
No!

49
00:05:42,380 --> 00:05:44,090
No, no, no! No!

50
00:05:55,850 --> 00:05:58,560
No! They expect one of us
in the wreckage, brother.

51
00:06:00,730 --> 00:06:02,190
Have we started the fire?

52
00:06:02,440 --> 00:06:05,940
Yes, the fire rises.

53
00:06:14,870 --> 00:06:18,460
Calm down, doctor. Now
is not the time for fear.

54
00:06:19,170 --> 00:06:20,830
That comes later.

55
00:06:47,490 --> 00:06:51,240
Harvey Dent Day may not be
our oldest public holiday

56
00:06:51,410 --> 00:06:54,450
but we're here tonight because
it's one of the most important.

57
00:06:54,620 --> 00:06:58,750
Harvey Dent's uncompromising
stand against organized crime

58
00:06:58,910 --> 00:07:00,450
had made Gotham a safer place

59
00:07:00,450 --> 00:07:03,040
than it was at the time of
his death, eight years ago.

60
00:07:03,210 --> 00:07:06,380
This city has seen a
historic turnaround.

61
00:07:06,590 --> 00:07:08,130
No city is without crime,

62
00:07:08,130 --> 00:07:10,610
but this city is without organized crime

63
00:07:10,610 --> 00:07:13,510
because the Dent Act
gave law enforcement teeth

64
00:07:13,510 --> 00:07:15,260
in its fight against the mob.

65
00:07:15,430 --> 00:07:19,100
Now people are talking
about repealing the Dent Act

66
00:07:19,270 --> 00:07:22,270
and to them I say, "Not on my watch."

67
00:07:23,770 --> 00:07:26,520
I want to thank the Wayne
Foundation for hosting this event.

68
00:07:26,690 --> 00:07:29,080
I'm told Mr. Wayne
couldn't be here tonight.

69
00:07:29,080 --> 00:07:30,820
I'm sure he's with us in spirit.

70
00:07:30,990 --> 00:07:33,740
And now I'm gonna give
way to an important voice

71
00:07:33,910 --> 00:07:36,370
You ever lay eyes on Wayne
at one of these things?

72
00:07:36,530 --> 00:07:38,240
No one has. Not in years.

73
00:07:38,410 --> 00:07:39,840
people put their faith

74
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:42,290
in a murderous thug
in a mask and a cape.

75
00:07:42,460 --> 00:07:46,000
A thug who showed his true nature

76
00:07:46,170 --> 00:07:48,630
when he betrayed the
trust of this great man

77
00:07:49,710 --> 00:07:51,300
and murdered him in cold blood.

78
00:07:52,010 --> 00:07:54,380
Sweetheart, not so fast with the chow.

79
00:07:54,550 --> 00:07:56,550
- Shrimp balls?
- Thank you.

80
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,880
Jim Gordon can tell you
the truth about Harvey Dent.

81
00:07:58,880 --> 00:08:00,180
I'll let him tell you himself.

82
00:08:00,350 --> 00:08:01,810
Commissioner Gordon.

83
00:08:11,150 --> 00:08:12,610
The truth?

84
00:08:17,490 --> 00:08:18,830
I have

85
00:08:20,120 --> 00:08:21,750
written a speech

86
00:08:22,960 --> 00:08:25,750
telling the truth about Harvey Dent.

87
00:08:30,710 --> 00:08:32,880
Maybe the time isn't right.

88
00:08:36,680 --> 00:08:39,260
Maybe right now

89
00:08:39,430 --> 00:08:41,450
all you need to know is that

90
00:08:41,450 --> 00:08:44,520
there are 1000 inmates
in Blackgate Prison

91
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:47,020
as a direct result of the Dent Act.

92
00:08:47,190 --> 00:08:49,050
These are violent criminals,

93
00:08:49,050 --> 00:08:52,110
essential cogs in the
organized- crime machine.

94
00:08:52,320 --> 00:08:54,490
Maybe, for now, all I should say

95
00:08:54,490 --> 00:08:57,200
about the death of Harvey Dent is this:

96
00:09:01,490 --> 00:09:02,700
It has not been for nothing.

97
00:09:04,960 --> 00:09:06,970
You see the guy who owns the house?

98
00:09:06,970 --> 00:09:09,360
No. I heard he never
leaves the east wing.

99
00:09:09,370 --> 00:09:10,840
I heard he had an accident.

100
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:14,760
- Yeah, that he's disfigured. He has to wear a...
- Mr. Till?

101
00:09:15,050 --> 00:09:18,640
Why are your people
using the main staircase?

102
00:09:19,220 --> 00:09:21,140
And where's Mrs. Bolton?

103
00:09:22,010 --> 00:09:24,020
Uh, she's at the bar, sir. Can I help?

104
00:09:24,180 --> 00:09:25,390
The east drawing room.

105
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:28,350
Unlock the door, put
the tray on the table,

106
00:09:28,360 --> 00:09:30,560
lock the door again. Nothing more.

107
00:09:34,610 --> 00:09:36,990
I'm sorry, Miss Tate. I
tried, but he won't see you.

108
00:09:37,360 --> 00:09:39,160
And you mustn't take it personally.

109
00:09:39,490 --> 00:09:42,420
Everyone knows that
Wayne's holed up in there

110
00:09:42,420 --> 00:09:45,160
with 8- inch nails
peeing into Mason jars.

111
00:09:45,330 --> 00:09:47,710
It's very good of you
to let me on the grounds.

112
00:10:00,050 --> 00:10:03,390
Why are you wasting your
time trying to talk to a man

113
00:10:03,560 --> 00:10:05,020
who threw away your

114
00:10:05,020 --> 00:10:08,270
investment on some
save- the- world vanity project?

115
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,690
He can't get your money back. I can.

116
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,920
I could try explaining

117
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:15,060
that a save- the- world
project,

118
00:10:15,060 --> 00:10:18,450
vain or not is worth
investing in, Mr. Daggett.

119
00:10:18,610 --> 00:10:21,780
But you understand only money
and the power you think it buys

120
00:10:21,990 --> 00:10:24,910
so why waste my time indeed?

121
00:10:25,450 --> 00:10:26,950
Second shift reports in?

122
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:29,210
You should spend more
time with the mayor.

123
00:10:29,370 --> 00:10:31,250
Well, that's your department.

124
00:10:32,250 --> 00:10:34,040
Anyone shown him the crime stats?

125
00:10:34,210 --> 00:10:36,140
He goes by his gut and it bothers him,

126
00:10:36,140 --> 00:10:37,510
no matter what the numbers.

127
00:10:37,670 --> 00:10:39,280
Must be popular with his wife.

128
00:10:39,280 --> 00:10:41,550
Not really. She took
the kids to Cleveland.

129
00:10:41,720 --> 00:10:43,720
He'll have plenty of time for visits.

130
00:10:43,720 --> 00:10:45,930
The mayor's gonna
dump him in the spring.

131
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,640
Really?

132
00:10:47,810 --> 00:10:51,690
- But he's a hero.
- A war hero. This is peacetime.

133
00:11:21,840 --> 00:11:25,220
Oh, sorry, sorry. I'm so
terribly sorry, Mr. Wayne.

134
00:11:27,680 --> 00:11:29,350
It is Mr. Wayne, isn't it?

135
00:11:31,100 --> 00:11:34,810
Although you don't
have the long nails or,

136
00:11:34,810 --> 00:11:37,190
heh, the facial scars, sir.

137
00:11:38,070 --> 00:11:40,190
Is that what they say about me?

138
00:11:40,570 --> 00:11:43,450
It's just that no one ever sees you.

139
00:11:43,950 --> 00:11:45,440
That's a beautiful necklace.

140
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:47,830
Reminds me of one that
belonged to my mother.

141
00:11:47,990 --> 00:11:51,080
It can't be the same one

142
00:11:51,580 --> 00:11:54,750
because her pearls are in this safe

143
00:11:56,040 --> 00:12:03,590
the manufacturer clearly
explained is uncrackable.

144
00:12:10,770 --> 00:12:12,980
Nobody told me it was uncrackable.

145
00:12:14,690 --> 00:12:17,150
I'm afraid I can't let you take those.

146
00:12:17,770 --> 00:12:19,770
Look, you wouldn't
beat up a woman any more

147
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:21,280
than I would beat up a cripple.

148
00:12:22,820 --> 00:12:26,160
Of course, sometimes
exceptions have to be made.

149
00:12:31,700 --> 00:12:33,500
Good night, Mr. Wayne.

150
00:12:48,680 --> 00:12:50,050
Can I have a ride?

151
00:12:50,560 --> 00:12:51,720
You read my mind.

152
00:12:52,520 --> 00:12:54,060
Let's go.

153
00:12:55,060 --> 00:12:56,850
Miss Tate was asking to see you again.

154
00:12:57,020 --> 00:12:58,650
She's very persistent.

155
00:12:58,810 --> 00:13:01,150
And quite lovely, in
case you were wondering.

156
00:13:01,320 --> 00:13:03,490
- I wasn't.
- What are you doing?

157
00:13:03,650 --> 00:13:06,950
Examining print dust. We've been robbed.

158
00:13:07,110 --> 00:13:10,070
And this is your idea of,
uh, sounding the alarm, is it?

159
00:13:10,240 --> 00:13:12,410
She took the pearls,
tracking device and all.

160
00:13:12,580 --> 00:13:13,870
- She?
- One of the maids.

161
00:13:14,040 --> 00:13:16,660
Perhaps you should stop letting
them in this side of the house.

162
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:19,290
Perhaps you should start
learning to make your own bed.

163
00:13:20,540 --> 00:13:23,380
- Why were you dusting for prints?
- I wasn't.

164
00:13:24,260 --> 00:13:25,720
She was.

165
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:32,060
Sir. Congressman Gilly's
wife has been calling in.

166
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:34,160
The congressman never made it home

167
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:36,100
after the Wayne Foundation event.

168
00:13:36,770 --> 00:13:38,440
That's a job for the police?

169
00:13:38,600 --> 00:13:41,440
When you and Dent cleaned the
streets, you cleaned them good.

170
00:13:41,610 --> 00:13:45,400
Pretty soon we'll be chasing
down, uh, overdue library books.

171
00:13:47,150 --> 00:13:51,320
And yet here you are,
like we're still at war.

172
00:13:53,290 --> 00:13:55,540
- What's your name, son?
- Blake, sir.

173
00:13:55,700 --> 00:13:57,500
You have something you want to ask me?

174
00:13:59,750 --> 00:14:00,790
It's about that night.

175
00:14:00,790 --> 00:14:03,090
This night, eight years
ago. The night Dent died.

176
00:14:03,250 --> 00:14:05,210
The last confirmed
sighting of the Batman.

177
00:14:05,670 --> 00:14:08,470
He murders those people,
takes down two SWAT teams

178
00:14:08,630 --> 00:14:12,390
breaks Dent's neck
and then just vanishes?

179
00:14:12,850 --> 00:14:15,180
I'm not hearing a question, son.

180
00:14:15,350 --> 00:14:17,310
Don't you want to know who he was?

181
00:14:18,190 --> 00:14:20,600
I know exactly who he was.

182
00:14:22,770 --> 00:14:24,570
He was the Batman.

183
00:14:26,780 --> 00:14:29,530
Let's go see about
the congressman's wife.

184
00:14:38,370 --> 00:14:39,830
Master Wayne?

185
00:14:41,630 --> 00:14:43,590
Master Wayne?

186
00:15:14,450 --> 00:15:16,830
You haven't been down
here in a long time.

187
00:15:16,990 --> 00:15:20,540
Trying to find out more about
our jewel thief. I ran her prints.

188
00:15:20,790 --> 00:15:22,500
Unless she's lost a lot of weight

189
00:15:23,790 --> 00:15:26,130
she was wearing someone
else's fingerprints.

190
00:15:26,300 --> 00:15:27,420
She's good.

191
00:15:27,590 --> 00:15:31,130
She may be, but we have
a trace on the necklace.

192
00:15:31,300 --> 00:15:34,490
We do. I cross- referenced
the address she went back

193
00:15:34,490 --> 00:15:37,680
to with police data on
high- end B- and- E's, and, um

194
00:15:38,180 --> 00:15:39,930
Selina Kyle.

195
00:15:40,100 --> 00:15:44,940
The databases are full of
close- calls, tips from fences.

196
00:15:45,110 --> 00:15:49,110
She's good, but the ground
is shrinking beneath her feet.

197
00:15:49,280 --> 00:15:52,030
We should send the police
before she fences the pearls.

198
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:54,410
She won't. She likes them too much.

199
00:15:54,570 --> 00:15:56,370
And they weren't what she was after.

200
00:15:56,530 --> 00:15:58,620
- What was she after?
- My fingerprints.

201
00:15:58,790 --> 00:16:01,790
It was printer toner mixed
with graphite on the safe.

202
00:16:01,960 --> 00:16:04,540
It gives a good pull
and it's untraceable.

203
00:16:04,710 --> 00:16:07,540
Fascinating. You two should
exchange notes over coffee.

204
00:16:07,710 --> 00:16:10,000
You're trying to set me
up with a jewel thief?

205
00:16:10,170 --> 00:16:12,720
At this point, I'd set
you up with a chimpanzee,

206
00:16:12,720 --> 00:16:14,630
if it brought you back to the world.

207
00:16:14,800 --> 00:16:17,050
There's nothing out there for me.

208
00:16:17,300 --> 00:16:18,810
And that's the problem.

209
00:16:18,970 --> 00:16:21,520
You hung up your cape and your
cowl but you didn't move on.

210
00:16:21,680 --> 00:16:23,980
You never went to find
a life. To find someone.

211
00:16:24,140 --> 00:16:25,520
Alfred

212
00:16:26,520 --> 00:16:28,310
I did find someone.

213
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:29,900
I know, and you lost them.

214
00:16:30,070 --> 00:16:32,030
But that's all part of living, sir.

215
00:16:32,190 --> 00:16:34,500
But you're not living,
you're just waiting,

216
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:36,320
hoping for things to go bad again.

217
00:16:36,530 --> 00:16:37,990
Remember when you left Gotham?

218
00:16:38,160 --> 00:16:41,160
Before all this, before Batman?

219
00:16:41,910 --> 00:16:42,950
You were gone seven years.

220
00:16:43,120 --> 00:16:47,710
Seven years I waited, hoping
that you wouldn't come back.

221
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:51,500
Every year, I took a
holiday. I went to Florence.

222
00:16:51,670 --> 00:16:53,920
There's this cafe on
the banks of the Arno.

223
00:16:54,090 --> 00:16:57,340
Every fine evening I'd sit
there and order a Fernet Branca.

224
00:16:58,180 --> 00:17:00,390
I had this fantasy

225
00:17:01,520 --> 00:17:04,180
that I would look across the tables

226
00:17:04,850 --> 00:17:08,310
and I'd see you there, with a wife.

227
00:17:08,520 --> 00:17:10,310
Maybe a couple of kids.

228
00:17:12,400 --> 00:17:16,280
You wouldn't say anything
to me, nor me to you.

229
00:17:17,570 --> 00:17:21,280
But we'd both know that you'd made it.

230
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,790
That you were happy.

231
00:17:26,670 --> 00:17:30,380
I never wanted you to
come back to Gotham.

232
00:17:31,550 --> 00:17:34,480
I always knew there was
nothing here for you,

233
00:17:34,480 --> 00:17:36,050
except pain and tragedy.

234
00:17:36,220 --> 00:17:39,090
And I wanted something
more for you than that.

235
00:17:44,100 --> 00:17:45,430
I still do.

236
00:17:49,690 --> 00:17:52,520
They wash up here a
couple of times a month.

237
00:17:52,690 --> 00:17:54,150
More when it gets colder.

238
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:56,280
Homeless, sheltering in the tunnels.

239
00:17:57,950 --> 00:17:59,680
We pulled him from the basin,

240
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:02,080
but other than that we didn't touch him.

241
00:18:04,450 --> 00:18:06,080
- What?
- Name's Jimmy.

242
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:07,660
He's from St. Swithin's.

243
00:18:08,290 --> 00:18:12,210
It's the boys' home
where I coach some ball.

244
00:18:15,010 --> 00:18:16,710
Jimmy hadn't been around for months.

245
00:18:16,880 --> 00:18:19,380
- No? Why?
- Blake, you know why.

246
00:18:19,550 --> 00:18:20,770
He aged out. We don't

247
00:18:20,770 --> 00:18:23,390
have the resources to
keep boys on after 16.

248
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:25,640
I thought the Wayne
Foundation gave money for that.

249
00:18:25,810 --> 00:18:27,890
Not for the past couple of years.

250
00:18:28,060 --> 00:18:31,900
- He has a brother here, doesn't he?
- Mark. I'll tell him.

251
00:18:32,060 --> 00:18:35,070
I'd like to, if that's all right.

252
00:18:36,190 --> 00:18:38,280
You know what he was
doing in the tunnels?

253
00:18:38,450 --> 00:18:42,280
Lot of guys been going down
the tunnels when they age out.

254
00:18:44,580 --> 00:18:46,660
Say you can live down there.

255
00:18:47,330 --> 00:18:48,870
Say there's work down there.

256
00:18:49,040 --> 00:18:50,540
Work?

257
00:18:50,830 --> 00:18:53,500
What kind of work are you
gonna find in the sewers?

258
00:18:53,670 --> 00:18:56,300
More than you can find up here, I guess.

259
00:18:57,170 --> 00:18:58,420
So you know about him?

260
00:18:58,590 --> 00:18:59,840
Of course.

261
00:19:01,550 --> 00:19:03,340
Do you think he's coming back?

262
00:19:05,560 --> 00:19:06,850
I don't know.

263
00:19:20,570 --> 00:19:22,240
You brought a date?

264
00:19:22,410 --> 00:19:25,620
I like having someone
around to open doors for me.

265
00:19:26,910 --> 00:19:29,750
Right hand. No partials.

266
00:19:33,670 --> 00:19:36,130
Very nice.

267
00:19:36,960 --> 00:19:39,010
Not so fast, handsome.

268
00:19:39,300 --> 00:19:40,550
You got something for me?

269
00:19:42,130 --> 00:19:43,630
Ah, yes.

270
00:19:53,190 --> 00:19:56,310
I don't know what you're planning
to do with Mr. Wayne's prints,

271
00:19:56,480 --> 00:19:59,280
but I'm guessing you'll need his thumb.

272
00:20:00,070 --> 00:20:02,150
You don't count so good, huh?

273
00:20:02,320 --> 00:20:03,570
I count fine.

274
00:20:03,990 --> 00:20:07,160
In fact, I'm counting to 10 right now.

275
00:20:09,620 --> 00:20:10,660
Okay.

276
00:20:14,790 --> 00:20:17,460
My friend's outside. Just hit "Send."

277
00:20:29,220 --> 00:20:30,560
This place is a little dead.

278
00:20:30,720 --> 00:20:33,980
It'll liven up in a minute. Trust me.

279
00:20:35,560 --> 00:20:36,690
Is everything okay?

280
00:20:36,860 --> 00:20:38,860
Great. Catch you later.

281
00:20:45,530 --> 00:20:50,240
It would have been a lot easier
to just give me what we agreed.

282
00:20:50,450 --> 00:20:52,830
We can't have loose ends.

283
00:20:53,080 --> 00:20:56,830
And even in that dress,
no one's gonna miss you.

284
00:20:57,000 --> 00:20:58,500
No.

285
00:20:58,670 --> 00:21:00,540
But my friend over there?

286
00:21:00,710 --> 00:21:03,880
Every cop in the city's missing him.

287
00:21:04,050 --> 00:21:05,380
That's cute.

288
00:21:05,550 --> 00:21:08,260
But they're not gonna be
looking in a place like this.

289
00:21:08,600 --> 00:21:11,350
I don't know. You did
just use his cell phone.

290
00:21:21,570 --> 00:21:22,940
- Go!
- Go!

291
00:21:39,250 --> 00:21:40,920
Police! Get down now!

292
00:21:44,210 --> 00:21:45,340
Help me! Help me!

293
00:21:45,510 --> 00:21:47,550
Help me, please! Please help me!

294
00:21:58,020 --> 00:22:00,350
Keep some pressure on that, sweetheart.

295
00:22:02,940 --> 00:22:04,070
Call me?

296
00:22:07,070 --> 00:22:09,320
- You okay, miss?
- He's bleeding. You gotta help him.

297
00:22:14,620 --> 00:22:15,700
I got the congressman.

298
00:22:44,650 --> 00:22:45,940
Clear!

299
00:22:50,070 --> 00:22:54,030
Manhole! Get this up!
Get the DWP down here!

300
00:22:54,990 --> 00:22:56,540
You three, down with me.

301
00:22:56,700 --> 00:23:00,120
You two, you go down,
cover the next exit!

302
00:23:16,810 --> 00:23:18,140
What, they went down there?

303
00:23:49,590 --> 00:23:51,240
We're gonna go down there, right?

304
00:23:51,250 --> 00:23:52,760
That was a gas explosion, kid.

305
00:23:52,930 --> 00:23:54,170
Wasn't gas. It's a sewer.

306
00:23:54,170 --> 00:23:56,180
No one goes in till
we know what's there.

307
00:23:56,350 --> 00:23:58,180
We know, sir. The police commissioner.

308
00:23:58,350 --> 00:24:00,180
Someone get this hothead out of here?

309
00:24:00,350 --> 00:24:02,850
And where's that DWP guy?

310
00:24:45,480 --> 00:24:47,440
Why are you here?

311
00:24:49,230 --> 00:24:50,770
Answer him.

312
00:24:52,440 --> 00:24:54,360
I was asking you.

313
00:24:54,740 --> 00:24:56,280
It's the police commissioner.

314
00:25:00,080 --> 00:25:02,540
And you brought him down here?

315
00:25:03,210 --> 00:25:05,790
- We didn't know what to do.
- You panicked.

316
00:25:06,330 --> 00:25:09,290
And your weakness has cost
the lives of three others.

317
00:25:09,460 --> 00:25:10,590
No, he's alone.

318
00:25:14,470 --> 00:25:16,010
Search him.

319
00:25:16,180 --> 00:25:17,720
Then I will kill you.

320
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:50,170
- He's dead.
- So show me his body.

321
00:25:50,340 --> 00:25:53,750
The water runs to any one of the
outflows. We'd never find him.

322
00:25:59,800 --> 00:26:01,970
- Follow him!
- Follow him?

323
00:26:17,740 --> 00:26:19,530
You okay? You okay?

324
00:26:19,700 --> 00:26:21,620
Hey, hey, you awake?

325
00:26:28,250 --> 00:26:29,870
I need to see Bruce Wayne.

326
00:26:30,040 --> 00:26:32,500
I'm sorry, Mr. Wayne doesn't
take unscheduled calls.

327
00:26:32,670 --> 00:26:34,460
Even from a police officer.

328
00:26:34,630 --> 00:26:35,920
And if I go get a warrant

329
00:26:35,920 --> 00:26:38,300
for the investigation
of Harvey Dent's murder?

330
00:26:38,470 --> 00:26:40,680
That still count as unscheduled?

331
00:26:44,850 --> 00:26:46,890
What can I do for you, officer?

332
00:26:47,230 --> 00:26:49,310
Commissioner Gordon's been shot.

333
00:26:51,650 --> 00:26:53,690
He chased a gunman down into the sewers.

334
00:26:53,860 --> 00:26:57,190
When I pulled him out, he was
babbling about an underground army.

335
00:26:57,360 --> 00:26:59,190
A masked man called Bane.

336
00:27:00,030 --> 00:27:02,360
Shouldn't you be telling
your superior officers?

337
00:27:02,530 --> 00:27:05,620
They asked me if he saw
any giant alligators.

338
00:27:06,080 --> 00:27:07,790
He needs you.

339
00:27:09,370 --> 00:27:10,660
He needs the Batman.

340
00:27:12,420 --> 00:27:14,340
If Commissioner Gordon thinks...

341
00:27:14,340 --> 00:27:16,210
he doesn't know or care who you are.

342
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:18,960
But we've met before.

343
00:27:20,090 --> 00:27:24,220
It was a long time ago. I
was a kid. Uh, St. Swithin's.

344
00:27:24,890 --> 00:27:28,600
It used to be funded by the Wayne
Foundation. It's an orphanage.

345
00:27:29,560 --> 00:27:31,070
My mom died when I was small.

346
00:27:31,080 --> 00:27:33,690
It was a car accident, I
don't really remember it.

347
00:27:34,310 --> 00:27:39,490
But my dad got shot a couple
years later over a gambling debt

348
00:27:39,740 --> 00:27:42,990
and I remember that one just fine.

349
00:27:44,320 --> 00:27:47,240
Not a lot of people know
what it feels like, do they?

350
00:27:47,620 --> 00:27:51,960
To be angry in your bones.

351
00:27:54,500 --> 00:27:56,670
I mean, they understand.

352
00:27:57,250 --> 00:27:58,670
Foster parents.

353
00:27:58,840 --> 00:28:00,840
Everybody understands

354
00:28:01,130 --> 00:28:02,630
for a while.

355
00:28:03,390 --> 00:28:05,260
And then they want the angry little kid

356
00:28:05,260 --> 00:28:07,100
to do something he knows he can't do.

357
00:28:07,680 --> 00:28:08,760
Move on.

358
00:28:09,350 --> 00:28:11,310
So after a while, they
stop understanding.

359
00:28:11,480 --> 00:28:13,350
They send the angry kid to a boys' home.

360
00:28:13,730 --> 00:28:17,520
I figured it out too late. You
gotta learn to hide the anger.

361
00:28:18,230 --> 00:28:20,570
Practice smiling in a mirror.

362
00:28:22,400 --> 00:28:23,900
It's like putting on a mask.

363
00:28:25,160 --> 00:28:28,700
So you showed up this
one day, in a cool car.

364
00:28:28,870 --> 00:28:30,700
Pretty girl on your arm.

365
00:28:31,790 --> 00:28:33,580
We were so excited.

366
00:28:33,870 --> 00:28:36,460
Bruce Wayne, billionaire orphan.

367
00:28:36,920 --> 00:28:40,670
I mean, we used to make up
stories about you, man. Legends.

368
00:28:40,840 --> 00:28:42,610
And, you know, with the other kids,

369
00:28:42,610 --> 00:28:44,630
that's all it was, just stories, but

370
00:28:46,260 --> 00:28:48,510
Right when I saw you, I
knew who you really were.

371
00:28:49,970 --> 00:28:52,770
I'd seen that look on your face before.

372
00:28:53,810 --> 00:28:55,940
It's the same one I taught myself.

373
00:28:57,900 --> 00:29:00,770
I don't know why you took
the fall for Dent's murder

374
00:29:01,650 --> 00:29:03,690
but I'm still a believer in the Batman

375
00:29:04,530 --> 00:29:06,200
even if you're not.

376
00:29:08,910 --> 00:29:10,860
Why did you say that your boys'

377
00:29:10,860 --> 00:29:13,830
home used to be funded
by the Wayne Foundation?

378
00:29:14,000 --> 00:29:15,750
Because the money stopped.

379
00:29:15,920 --> 00:29:17,960
Might be time to get some fresh air.

380
00:29:17,970 --> 00:29:20,130
Start paying attention to the details.

381
00:29:21,000 --> 00:29:23,380
Some of those details
might need your help.

382
00:29:25,180 --> 00:29:26,510
You check that name? Bane?

383
00:29:26,680 --> 00:29:29,340
He's a mercenary. No other known names.

384
00:29:29,510 --> 00:29:31,970
Him and his men were
behind a coup in West Africa

385
00:29:32,140 --> 00:29:36,640
that secured mining operations
for our friend John Daggett.

386
00:29:37,350 --> 00:29:40,150
- Now Daggett's brought them here.
- Or so it seems.

387
00:29:42,230 --> 00:29:44,360
- I'll keep digging.
- Yeah.

388
00:29:45,570 --> 00:29:47,700
Alfred, why did the Wayne

389
00:29:47,700 --> 00:29:51,780
Foundation stop funding
boys' homes in the city?

390
00:29:51,950 --> 00:29:57,040
The foundation is funded by the
profits of Wayne Enterprises.

391
00:29:57,370 --> 00:29:58,920
There have to be some.

392
00:29:59,080 --> 00:30:02,420
- Time to talk to Mr. Fox, I think.
- I'll get him on the phone.

393
00:30:02,590 --> 00:30:06,590
No, no, no. Do we still have
any cars around the place?

394
00:30:06,760 --> 00:30:08,630
Yes. One or two.

395
00:30:08,800 --> 00:30:10,800
I need an appointment at
the hospital for my leg.

396
00:30:10,970 --> 00:30:13,720
- Which hospital?
- Whichever one Jim Gordon's in.

397
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:20,900
- I have seen worse cartilage in knees.
- That's good.

398
00:30:21,060 --> 00:30:23,570
No. That's because there is
no cartilage in your knee.

399
00:30:23,730 --> 00:30:27,070
And not much of any use in
your elbows or your shoulders.

400
00:30:27,240 --> 00:30:29,610
Between that and the scar
tissue on your kidneys

401
00:30:29,780 --> 00:30:32,450
the residual concussive
damage to your brain tissue

402
00:30:32,620 --> 00:30:35,290
and the general scarred- over
quality of your body

403
00:30:35,450 --> 00:30:38,370
- I cannot recommend that
you go heli- skiing. - Right.

404
00:30:53,850 --> 00:30:56,350
We were in this together

405
00:30:58,480 --> 00:31:00,020
then you were gone.

406
00:31:00,190 --> 00:31:02,310
The Batman wasn't needed anymore.

407
00:31:02,480 --> 00:31:05,610
- We won.
- Based on a lie.

408
00:31:07,070 --> 00:31:13,120
And now there's evil rising
from where we tried to bury it.

409
00:31:13,320 --> 00:31:17,790
The Batman has to come back.

410
00:31:17,950 --> 00:31:20,410
What if he doesn't exist anymore?

411
00:31:20,580 --> 00:31:24,040
He must.

412
00:31:37,770 --> 00:31:39,600
You took my goddamn wallet, didn't you?

413
00:31:39,770 --> 00:31:42,640
- You f... You took my wallet!
- No, I

414
00:31:43,350 --> 00:31:45,560
- Get out.
- She took my... Ah!

415
00:31:45,730 --> 00:31:48,320
- Now.
- Creep!

416
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:50,120
I don't know what he's so upset about.

417
00:31:50,120 --> 00:31:51,400
There's only 60 bucks in here.

418
00:31:51,570 --> 00:31:53,320
Probably the watch.

419
00:32:08,590 --> 00:32:09,630
Who's that?

420
00:32:09,800 --> 00:32:11,920
A stiff can barely climb
out of his sports car.

421
00:32:12,090 --> 00:32:14,220
- No, that's Bruce Wayne!
- Mr. Wayne, over here!

422
00:32:19,270 --> 00:32:21,640
I'm not sure if my assistant...
- Right through here.

423
00:32:21,810 --> 00:32:23,310
Thank you so much.

424
00:32:28,570 --> 00:32:32,360
Bruce Wayne at a charity ball.

425
00:32:33,400 --> 00:32:35,280
Miss Tate, isn't it?

426
00:32:36,280 --> 00:32:39,330
Even before you became a recluse,
you never came to these things.

427
00:32:39,790 --> 00:32:43,160
The proceeds go to the big fat
spread. It's not about charity.

428
00:32:43,330 --> 00:32:47,670
It's about feeding the ego of
whichever society hag laid this on.

429
00:32:48,170 --> 00:32:50,590
Actually, this is my party, Mr. Wayne.

430
00:32:52,800 --> 00:32:55,310
And the proceeds will
go where they should,

431
00:32:55,310 --> 00:32:57,930
because I paid for the
big fat spread myself.

432
00:32:58,350 --> 00:32:59,720
That's very generous of you.

433
00:32:59,970 --> 00:33:03,810
You have to invest if you want
to restore balance to the world.

434
00:33:03,980 --> 00:33:05,730
Take our clean- energy project.

435
00:33:06,270 --> 00:33:08,900
Sometimes the investment
doesn't pay off.

436
00:33:09,690 --> 00:33:13,360
- I'm sorry.
- You have a practiced apathy, Mr. Wayne.

437
00:33:13,530 --> 00:33:15,480
But a man who doesn't care about

438
00:33:15,480 --> 00:33:18,660
the world doesn't spend
half his fortune to save it.

439
00:33:19,660 --> 00:33:22,660
And isn't so wounded when it fails

440
00:33:23,080 --> 00:33:24,710
that he goes into hiding.

441
00:33:26,170 --> 00:33:28,250
Have a good evening, Mr. Wayne.

442
00:33:32,300 --> 00:33:33,960
Mind if I cut in?

443
00:33:35,050 --> 00:33:36,880
Thank you.

444
00:33:39,760 --> 00:33:41,280
You don't seem happy to see me.

445
00:33:41,280 --> 00:33:42,930
You were supposed to be a shut- in.

446
00:33:43,100 --> 00:33:44,980
I felt like some fresh air.

447
00:33:45,770 --> 00:33:47,890
Why didn't you call the police?

448
00:33:48,230 --> 00:33:50,900
I have a powerful friend who
deals with things like this.

449
00:33:51,070 --> 00:33:55,360
That's a brazen costume
for a cat burglar.

450
00:33:55,900 --> 00:33:58,490
Yeah? Who are you pretending to be?

451
00:33:58,660 --> 00:34:01,370
Bruce Wayne, eccentric billionaire.

452
00:34:02,450 --> 00:34:04,450
- Who's your date?
- His wife's in Ibiza.

453
00:34:04,620 --> 00:34:08,420
She left her diamonds behind,
though. Worried they might get stolen.

454
00:34:08,580 --> 00:34:10,630
It's pronounced "Ibiza."

455
00:34:11,210 --> 00:34:12,610
You wouldn't want these folks

456
00:34:12,610 --> 00:34:14,880
realizing you're a crook,
not a social climber.

457
00:34:15,050 --> 00:34:18,180
You think I care what anyone
in this room thinks of me?

458
00:34:19,840 --> 00:34:22,180
I doubt you care what anyone
in any room thinks of you.

459
00:34:22,350 --> 00:34:26,060
Don't condescend, Mr. Wayne.
You don't know a thing about me.

460
00:34:26,680 --> 00:34:30,900
Well, Selina Kyle, I know you came
here from your walk- up in Old Town.

461
00:34:31,060 --> 00:34:32,900
A modest place for a master jewel thief.

462
00:34:33,070 --> 00:34:36,360
Which means that either
you're saving for retirement

463
00:34:36,990 --> 00:34:39,070
or you're in deep with the wrong people.

464
00:34:40,410 --> 00:34:41,960
You don't get to judge me because

465
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:44,370
you were born in the master
bedroom of Wayne Manor.

466
00:34:44,540 --> 00:34:46,900
Actually, I was born
in the Regency Room.

467
00:34:46,900 --> 00:34:48,870
I started out doing what I had to.

468
00:34:50,040 --> 00:34:51,590
Once you've done what you had to,

469
00:34:51,590 --> 00:34:53,420
they never let you do what you want to.

470
00:34:53,590 --> 00:34:54,840
Start fresh.

471
00:34:55,000 --> 00:34:58,220
Ugh. There's no fresh
start in today's world.

472
00:34:58,380 --> 00:35:01,430
Any 12- year- old with a cell
phone could find out what you did.

473
00:35:01,590 --> 00:35:05,390
Everything we do is collated and
quantified. Everything sticks.

474
00:35:05,970 --> 00:35:07,970
Is that how you justify stealing?

475
00:35:08,140 --> 00:35:10,730
I take what I need from those
who have more than enough.

476
00:35:10,900 --> 00:35:13,190
I don't stand on the
shoulders of people with less.

477
00:35:13,360 --> 00:35:14,400
Robin Hood?

478
00:35:14,570 --> 00:35:16,330
I think I'd do more to help someone

479
00:35:16,330 --> 00:35:18,690
than most of the people
in this room. Than you.

480
00:35:19,650 --> 00:35:21,740
You think maybe you're
assuming a little too much?

481
00:35:21,910 --> 00:35:23,580
Maybe you're being unrealistic about

482
00:35:23,580 --> 00:35:25,950
what's really in your pants
other than your wallet.

483
00:35:26,120 --> 00:35:27,160
Ouch.

484
00:35:27,660 --> 00:35:32,750
You think all this can last?
There's a storm coming, Mr. Wayne.

485
00:35:33,380 --> 00:35:36,690
You and your friends better
batten down the hatches,

486
00:35:36,690 --> 00:35:40,880
because when it hits you're all
gonna wonder how you ever thought

487
00:35:40,880 --> 00:35:42,410
you could live so large

488
00:35:42,410 --> 00:35:44,890
and leave so little for the rest of us.

489
00:35:48,180 --> 00:35:50,680
You sound like you're
looking forward to it.

490
00:35:52,100 --> 00:35:53,690
I'm adaptable.

491
00:35:53,860 --> 00:35:57,110
Those pearls do look better on
you than they did in my safe.

492
00:35:57,860 --> 00:36:00,070
But I still can't let you keep them.

493
00:36:07,740 --> 00:36:09,910
You... You scared her off!

494
00:36:12,830 --> 00:36:14,370
Not likely.

495
00:36:16,500 --> 00:36:17,880
Must have lost my ticket.

496
00:36:18,050 --> 00:36:20,800
- Your wife said you were taking a cab home.
- My wife?

497
00:36:28,850 --> 00:36:30,270
Just you, sir?

498
00:36:33,350 --> 00:36:35,350
Don't worry, Master Wayne.

499
00:36:36,110 --> 00:36:39,150
Takes a little time to get
back in the swing of things.

500
00:36:41,320 --> 00:36:44,570
Bruce Wayne, as I live and breathe.

501
00:36:46,370 --> 00:36:48,740
What brings you out of
cryo- sleep, Mr. Wayne?

502
00:36:48,910 --> 00:36:50,660
You haven't lost your sense of humor.

503
00:36:50,830 --> 00:36:53,330
Even if you have lost most of my money.

504
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:55,000
Actually, you did that.

505
00:36:55,170 --> 00:36:57,880
If you funnel your entire R and D budget

506
00:36:58,040 --> 00:37:00,960
into a fusion project
that you then mothball

507
00:37:01,130 --> 00:37:03,470
your company is unlikely to thrive.

508
00:37:03,630 --> 00:37:04,670
What are my options?

509
00:37:04,840 --> 00:37:07,220
Well, if you're unwilling
to turn on the machine

510
00:37:08,100 --> 00:37:09,930
I can't. I can't, Lucius.

511
00:37:10,510 --> 00:37:12,060
Well, then sit tight.

512
00:37:12,230 --> 00:37:14,480
Your majority keeps Daggett at bay while

