723
00:55:04,130 --> 00:55:05,830
In return, I need to know

724
00:55:05,830 --> 00:55:08,880
what you did with Bruce
Wayne's fingerprints.

725
00:55:09,050 --> 00:55:11,590
Wayne wasn't kidding
about a powerful friend.

726
00:55:12,760 --> 00:55:16,690
I sold his prints to
Daggett for something

727
00:55:16,690 --> 00:55:19,060
that doesn't even exist.

728
00:55:19,350 --> 00:55:21,450
I doubt many people
get the better of you.

729
00:55:21,450 --> 00:55:23,060
Hey, when a girl's desperate

730
00:55:23,230 --> 00:55:25,570
- What's he gonna do with them?
- I don't know

731
00:55:25,730 --> 00:55:27,050
but Daggett seemed pretty

732
00:55:27,050 --> 00:55:29,110
interested in that mess
at the stock market.

733
00:55:34,370 --> 00:55:35,830
Miss Kyle?

734
00:55:38,750 --> 00:55:40,960
So that's what that feels like.

735
00:56:00,270 --> 00:56:02,060
I see from the television coverage

736
00:56:02,070 --> 00:56:04,810
that you got your taste
for wanton destruction back.

737
00:56:04,980 --> 00:56:06,940
I retrieved this.

738
00:56:07,110 --> 00:56:09,570
Aren't the police supposed
to be investigating, then?

739
00:56:09,740 --> 00:56:11,530
They don't have the tools to analyze it.

740
00:56:11,530 --> 00:56:13,160
They would if you gave them to them.

741
00:56:13,320 --> 00:56:15,820
One man's tool is another man's weapon.

742
00:56:15,990 --> 00:56:16,920
In your mind, perhaps.

743
00:56:16,920 --> 00:56:19,330
But there aren't many things
you can't turn into a weapon.

744
00:56:19,500 --> 00:56:21,620
Alfred, enough. The police
weren't getting it done.

745
00:56:21,790 --> 00:56:22,980
Perhaps they might have

746
00:56:22,990 --> 00:56:25,170
if you hadn't made a
sideshow of yourself.

747
00:56:25,340 --> 00:56:27,020
You thought I didn't have it in me.

748
00:56:27,020 --> 00:56:29,130
You led a bloated
police force on a chase

749
00:56:29,300 --> 00:56:31,880
with a load of fancy new toys from Fox.

750
00:56:32,050 --> 00:56:34,890
What about when you come
up against him? What then?

751
00:56:35,050 --> 00:56:37,120
I'll fight harder. I always have.

752
00:56:37,120 --> 00:56:39,850
Look. His speed, his
ferocity, his training.

753
00:56:40,020 --> 00:56:42,680
I see the power of belief.

754
00:56:42,850 --> 00:56:45,770
I see the League of Shadows resurgent.

755
00:56:45,940 --> 00:56:47,400
You said he was excommunicated.

756
00:56:47,570 --> 00:56:49,440
By Ra's Al Ghul.

757
00:56:50,490 --> 00:56:51,570
Who leads them now?

758
00:56:51,740 --> 00:56:54,320
Ra's Al Ghul was the League
of Shadows and I beat him.

759
00:56:54,490 --> 00:56:57,240
Bane is a mercenary. We need
to find out what he's up to.

760
00:56:58,450 --> 00:57:00,990
Trades of some kind. Coded.

761
00:57:01,830 --> 00:57:04,620
And my fingerprint,
courtesy of Selina Kyle.

762
00:57:04,790 --> 00:57:05,870
Get this to Fox.

763
00:57:06,040 --> 00:57:07,450
He can crack the code

764
00:57:07,450 --> 00:57:10,380
and tell us what trades
they were executing.

765
00:57:14,050 --> 00:57:17,720
I'll get this to Mr. Fox, but no more.

766
00:57:19,390 --> 00:57:22,930
I've sewn you up, I've set your
bones, but I won't bury you.

767
00:57:23,350 --> 00:57:26,480
I've buried enough members
of the Wayne family.

768
00:57:27,270 --> 00:57:32,610
- You'll leave me?
- You see only one end to your journey.

769
00:57:33,070 --> 00:57:37,660
Leaving is all I have
to make you understand.

770
00:57:37,950 --> 00:57:41,450
You're not Batman anymore.
You have to find another way.

771
00:57:41,620 --> 00:57:43,510
You used to talk about finishing,

