00:57:43,510 --> 00:57:45,580
about a life beyond that awful cave.

773
00:57:45,750 --> 00:57:49,460
Alfred, Rachel died knowing that
we had decided to be together.

774
00:57:49,630 --> 00:57:53,510
That was my life beyond the
cave. I can't just move on.

775
00:57:53,970 --> 00:57:56,800
She... She didn't. She couldn't.

776
00:57:57,640 --> 00:57:59,010
What if she had?

777
00:57:59,180 --> 00:58:00,640
She... I can't change that.

778
00:58:00,810 --> 00:58:03,810
What if before she
died she wrote a letter

779
00:58:03,980 --> 00:58:07,440
saying she chose Harvey Dent over you?

780
00:58:11,820 --> 00:58:16,070
And what if to spare you pain,

781
00:58:17,910 --> 00:58:19,780
I burnt that letter?

782
00:58:20,620 --> 00:58:24,830
How dare you use Rachel
to try to stop me?

783
00:58:25,040 --> 00:58:28,460
I am using the truth, Master Wayne.

784
00:58:29,130 --> 00:58:32,530
Maybe it's time we all stopped
trying to outsmart the truth

785
00:58:32,530 --> 00:58:34,000
and let it have its day.

786
00:58:35,630 --> 00:58:37,760
- I'm sorry.
- You're sorry?

787
00:58:37,930 --> 00:58:40,640
You expect to destroy my world

788
00:58:43,010 --> 00:58:45,390
and then think that
we're gonna shake hands?

789
00:58:45,560 --> 00:58:47,230
No, no, no.

790
00:58:48,480 --> 00:58:50,560
I know what this means.

791
00:58:50,730 --> 00:58:51,810
What does it mean?

792
00:58:51,980 --> 00:58:54,400
It means your hatred.

793
00:58:54,610 --> 00:58:59,690
And it also means losing
someone that I have cared

794
00:58:59,690 --> 00:59:05,660
for since I first heard his
cries echo through this house.

795
00:59:06,000 --> 00:59:10,250
But it might also mean saving your life.

796
00:59:11,540 --> 00:59:13,960
And that is more important.

797
00:59:19,180 --> 00:59:20,220
Goodbye, Alfred.

798
00:59:39,990 --> 00:59:41,200
Alfred?

799
00:59:46,410 --> 00:59:49,000
- Answering your own door?
- Yeah.

800
00:59:50,420 --> 00:59:51,710
Page three.

801
00:59:52,250 --> 00:59:53,740
Seems you made a series of

802
00:59:53,740 --> 00:59:56,250
large put options on
the futures exchange

803
00:59:56,420 --> 00:59:57,710
verified by thumbprint.

804
00:59:57,880 --> 01:00:00,550
Those options expired
at midnight last night.

805
01:00:00,720 --> 01:00:03,300
Long- term, we may be
able to prove fraud.

806
01:00:03,300 --> 01:00:05,760
But for now, you're completely broke

807
01:00:05,930 --> 01:00:07,210
and Wayne Enterprises is

808
01:00:07,210 --> 01:00:09,350
about to fall into the
hands of John Daggett.

809
01:00:09,520 --> 01:00:10,230
The weapons.

810
01:00:10,230 --> 01:00:13,350
We can't let Daggett get his
hands on Applied Sciences.

811
01:00:13,520 --> 01:00:16,480
Applied Sciences is all
locked up and off the books.

812
01:00:16,650 --> 01:00:19,860
The energy project, however,
is a different story.

813
01:00:20,030 --> 01:00:21,530
Miranda Tate.

814
01:00:22,530 --> 01:00:24,550
Let's convince the
board to get behind her.

815
01:00:24,550 --> 01:00:25,820
Let's show her the reactor.

816
01:00:25,990 --> 01:00:29,490
We're meeting her there in 35
minutes, so you better get dressed.

817
01:00:29,830 --> 01:00:33,370
You brought me out here
to show me this, Mr. Fox?

818
01:00:33,580 --> 01:00:35,540
Bear with me, Miss Tate.

819
01:00:39,260 --> 01:00:42,720
Please keep hands and feet
inside the car at all times.

820
01:00:48,310 --> 01:00:50,100
This is it, isn't it?

821
01:00:50,680 --> 01:00:53,270
The reactor is beneath the river

822
01:00:53,810 --> 01:00:55,210
so it can be instantly

823
01:00:55,210 --> 01:00:57,560
flooded in the event
of a security breach.

824
01:00:58,270 --> 01:01:01,190
Is Bruce Wayne really that paranoid?

825
01:01:01,360 --> 01:01:03,650
I'm gonna plead the fifth on that one.

826
01:01:10,540 --> 01:01:13,460
I thought you might like to
see what your investment built.

827
01:01:13,620 --> 01:01:15,290
No fossil fuels.

828
01:01:15,460 --> 01:01:18,040
Free clean energy for an entire city.

829
01:01:18,210 --> 01:01:21,760
Three years ago, a Russian
scientist published a paper

830
01:01:21,920 --> 01:01:24,220
on weaponized fusion reactions.

831
01:01:24,380 --> 01:01:29,300
One week later, your reactor
started developing problems.

832
01:01:30,560 --> 01:01:32,180
I think this machine works.

833
01:01:32,350 --> 01:01:35,300
Miranda, if it were operational,

834
01:01:35,300 --> 01:01:38,980
the danger to Gotham would be too great.

835
01:01:39,150 --> 01:01:41,360
Would it make you feel better to know

836
01:01:41,360 --> 01:01:45,200
that the Russian scientist died
in a plane crash six months ago?

837
01:01:45,360 --> 01:01:48,870
Someone will work out
what Dr. Pavel did.

838
01:01:49,030 --> 01:01:51,360
Someone will figure out a way

839
01:01:51,360 --> 01:01:55,210
to make this power source
into a nuclear weapon.

840
01:01:56,540 --> 01:02:02,630
I need you to take control of
Wayne Enterprises and this reactor.

841
01:02:03,050 --> 01:02:04,170
To do what with it?

842
01:02:04,340 --> 01:02:05,840
Nothing.

843
01:02:06,430 --> 01:02:08,550
Until we can guarantee its safety.

844
01:02:08,720 --> 01:02:09,930
And if we can't?

845
01:02:10,220 --> 01:02:11,760
Decommission it. Flood it.

846
01:02:11,930 --> 01:02:15,730
Destroy the world's best
chance for a sustainable future?

847
01:02:15,890 --> 01:02:17,520
If the world's not ready, yes.

848
01:02:17,690 --> 01:02:20,060
Bruce, if you want to save the world,

849
01:02:20,060 --> 01:02:21,980
you have to start trusting it.

850
01:02:22,360 --> 01:02:23,730
I'm trusting you.

851
01:02:23,900 --> 01:02:25,860
Doesn't count. You have no choice.

852
01:02:26,610 --> 01:02:28,950
I could have flooded
this chamber at any time.

853
01:02:29,120 --> 01:02:31,160
I'm choosing to trust you.

854
01:02:32,030 --> 01:02:33,240
Please.

855
01:02:40,500 --> 01:02:42,420
All right, ladies and gentlemen.

856
01:02:42,430 --> 01:02:44,590
This meeting will now come to order.

857
01:02:44,760 --> 01:02:47,920
I'd like to point out that we
have a non- board member here

858
01:02:48,090 --> 01:02:49,450
which is highly irregular,

859
01:02:49,460 --> 01:02:51,430
even if his family
name is above the door.

860
01:02:51,600 --> 01:02:53,850
Bruce Wayne's family built this company.

861
01:02:54,020 --> 01:02:55,770
And he himself has run it.

862
01:02:55,930 --> 01:02:58,580
Into the ground, sir!
Does anybody disagree?

863
01:02:58,580 --> 01:03:00,690
Check the share price this morning.

864
01:03:00,860 --> 01:03:05,110
Crazy gambling on futures has
not only cost Mr. Wayne his seat

865
01:03:05,280 --> 01:03:07,570
it's cost us all a lot of money.

866
01:03:07,740 --> 01:03:09,570
And he has to go.

867
01:03:10,450 --> 01:03:12,450
I'm afraid he has a point, Mr. Wayne.

868
01:03:20,880 --> 01:03:22,540
Now, back to business.

869
01:03:23,250 --> 01:03:24,270
Mr. Wayne, over here!

870
01:03:24,270 --> 01:03:26,460
How's it feel to be one of the people?

871
01:03:26,630 --> 01:03:28,400
Mr. Wayne, they're towing your car!

872
01:03:28,400 --> 01:03:30,680
I didn't know what to
do, they had paperwork.

873
01:03:32,430 --> 01:03:34,140
Looks like you need a ride, huh?

874
01:03:34,310 --> 01:03:36,520
Wayne, we'll give you a ride!

875
01:03:36,680 --> 01:03:38,470
How the hell did Miranda Tate

876
01:03:38,470 --> 01:03:40,980
get the inside track on the Wayne board?

877
01:03:41,150 --> 01:03:43,310
She been meeting with
him? Sleeping with him?

878
01:03:43,480 --> 01:03:46,440
- Not that we know of.
- You don't know much of anything, do you?

879
01:03:46,610 --> 01:03:48,530
- Where's Bane?
- We told him it was urgent.

880
01:03:48,690 --> 01:03:51,320
- Where is that masked...?
- Speak of the devil

881
01:03:51,490 --> 01:03:53,740
and he shall appear.

882
01:03:53,910 --> 01:03:56,370
What the hell is going on?

883
01:03:56,990 --> 01:04:00,370
- The plan is proceeding as expected.
- Oh, really?

884
01:04:00,540 --> 01:04:03,330
Do I look like I'm running
Wayne Enterprises right now?

885
01:04:03,630 --> 01:04:08,170
Your hit on the stock exchange,
it didn't work, my friend.

886
01:04:08,340 --> 01:04:10,810
And now you have my construction crews

887
01:04:10,810 --> 01:04:13,470
going around the city at 24 hours a day.

888
01:04:13,640 --> 01:04:18,560
How exactly is that supposed to
help my company absorb Wayne's?

889
01:04:21,140 --> 01:04:23,520
- Leave us.
- No. You stay here.

890
01:04:23,690 --> 01:04:25,270
I'm in charge.

891
01:04:26,070 --> 01:04:28,440
Do you feel in charge?

892
01:04:33,490 --> 01:04:35,240
I've paid you a small fortune.

893
01:04:35,410 --> 01:04:38,370
And this gives you power over me?

894
01:04:38,950 --> 01:04:40,370
What is this?

895
01:04:40,540 --> 01:04:45,500
Your money and infrastructure
have been important

896
01:04:45,880 --> 01:04:47,000
till now.

897
01:04:47,500 --> 01:04:48,630
What are you?

898
01:04:48,800 --> 01:04:50,630
I'm Gotham's reckoning.

899
01:04:50,800 --> 01:04:53,680
Here to end the borrowed time
you've all been living on.

900
01:04:55,720 --> 01:04:58,850
You're pure evil.

901
01:04:59,020 --> 01:05:01,310
I'm necessary evil.

902
01:05:01,480 --> 01:05:03,390
No. No, no, no!

903
01:05:07,980 --> 01:05:10,440
When you started, why the mask?

904
01:05:10,610 --> 01:05:12,110
To protect the people closest to me.

905
01:05:12,110 --> 01:05:13,280
But you were a loner, right?

906
01:05:13,450 --> 01:05:14,730
You didn't have any family?

907
01:05:14,730 --> 01:05:16,570
There are always people you care about.

908
01:05:16,740 --> 01:05:20,660
You just don't realize how
much until they're gone.

909
01:05:21,080 --> 01:05:23,960
The idea was to be a symbol.

910
01:05:24,120 --> 01:05:27,250
Batman could be anybody.

911
01:05:27,790 --> 01:05:29,340
That was the point.

912
01:05:29,710 --> 01:05:32,920
- Well, it was damn good to see him back.
- Not everybody agrees.

913
01:05:33,130 --> 01:05:35,130
They'll figure that out in the end.

914
01:05:35,130 --> 01:05:37,340
You got anything on Bane's whereabouts?

915
01:05:37,890 --> 01:05:41,100
Yeah. I got 500 pages of
tunnel records and a flashlight.

916
01:05:41,270 --> 01:05:43,350
I could use some help, actually.

917
01:05:44,350 --> 01:05:46,230
You know what? Drop me in Old Town.

918
01:05:49,860 --> 01:05:51,440
Hey, hey, hey. I don't think so!

919
01:05:51,610 --> 01:05:53,780
- That's the way this works!
- I don't think so!

920
01:05:53,950 --> 01:05:56,200
- That is the way...
- He's not a mark.

921
01:05:56,360 --> 01:05:59,030
And he doesn't have a
cent to his name, anyway.

922
01:05:59,530 --> 01:06:03,830
Yeah, it's not much. But it's
more than you've got right now.

923
01:06:04,000 --> 01:06:06,410
Actually, they're
letting me keep the house.

924
01:06:06,580 --> 01:06:09,170
The rich don't even go broke
the same as the rest of us, huh?

925
01:06:09,340 --> 01:06:13,300
My powerful friend might hope to
change your mind about leaving.

926
01:06:13,460 --> 01:06:16,090
- And how would he do that?
- By giving you what you want.

927
01:06:16,260 --> 01:06:18,930
- It doesn't exist.
- He says it does.

928
01:06:19,640 --> 01:06:21,350
He wants to meet tonight.

929
01:06:21,510 --> 01:06:22,560
Why?

930
01:06:22,720 --> 01:06:25,640
He needs to find Bane.
Says you'd know how.

931
01:06:28,980 --> 01:06:31,190
- Tell him I'll think about it.
- Okay.

932
01:06:31,360 --> 01:06:33,230
I like your place.

933
01:06:34,690 --> 01:06:35,820
Mr. Wayne?

934
01:06:38,450 --> 01:06:40,700
I'm sorry they took all your money.

935
01:06:41,780 --> 01:06:43,080
No, you're not.

936
01:06:44,200 --> 01:06:47,000
- Can we help you, officer?
- Uh, yeah.

937
01:06:47,160 --> 01:06:48,400
John Daggett's body was

938
01:06:48,400 --> 01:06:50,710
just found in a Dumpster
about an hour ago.

939
01:06:50,880 --> 01:06:52,840
- Thought you might want to know.
- Why?

940
01:06:53,000 --> 01:06:55,510
His name's all over these
permits I just pulled to,

941
01:06:55,510 --> 01:06:57,130
uh, map the tunnels under Gotham.

942
01:06:57,300 --> 01:06:58,790
That's MTA maintenance, uh,

943
01:06:58,800 --> 01:07:01,180
sewer construction,
couple of other things.

944
01:07:01,350 --> 01:07:04,350
Where did you get to
with the tunnel searches?

945
01:07:04,520 --> 01:07:07,390
Remind me to tell detail
to keep hotheads out.

946
01:07:07,560 --> 01:07:09,730
We've had teams down
there. It's a huge network.

947
01:07:09,900 --> 01:07:13,230
Well, get more men. Work
a grid. I want him found.

948
01:07:13,400 --> 01:07:15,730
Yeah, the, uh, masked man. We're on it.

949
01:07:15,900 --> 01:07:18,650
Lose the uniform, you're
working for me now.

950
01:07:18,820 --> 01:07:21,240
We could use some
hotter heads around here.

951
01:07:21,410 --> 01:07:23,770
Sir, that could also be a coincidence.

952
01:07:23,780 --> 01:07:25,540
You're a detective now, son.

953
01:07:25,700 --> 01:07:28,830
You're not allowed to believe
in coincidence anymore.

954
01:07:40,010 --> 01:07:41,550
Nobody's answering.

955
01:07:41,930 --> 01:07:43,090
No.

956
01:07:43,260 --> 01:07:44,930
I'm on my own now.

957
01:07:45,770 --> 01:07:47,180
Do you have keys?

958
01:07:48,390 --> 01:07:49,560
Never needed them.

959
01:07:56,230 --> 01:07:57,980
Hope you didn't like me for my money.

960
01:07:58,740 --> 01:08:01,320
Suffering builds character.

961
01:08:07,370 --> 01:08:09,910
I'll take care of your
parents' legacy, Bruce.

962
01:08:12,080 --> 01:08:13,420
Who's this?

963
01:08:21,260 --> 01:08:22,590
Where's Alfred?

964
01:08:24,390 --> 01:08:25,760
He left

965
01:08:27,430 --> 01:08:29,390
taking everything.

966
01:08:53,370 --> 01:08:54,750
What's that?

967
01:08:55,540 --> 01:08:57,840
My power's been shut off.

968
01:09:03,340 --> 01:09:04,800
You're good at that.

969
01:09:05,930 --> 01:09:08,850
When I was a child,
we had almost nothing.

970
01:09:09,310 --> 01:09:13,810
But on the nights when we had a
fire, we felt very rich indeed.

971
01:09:15,650 --> 01:09:18,610
I assumed your family was wealthy.

972
01:09:19,400 --> 01:09:20,900
Not always.

973
01:09:21,900 --> 01:09:23,440
Not when I was young.

974
01:09:24,110 --> 01:09:25,950
An old mistake.

975
01:09:27,070 --> 01:09:28,950
I've made a few myself.

976
01:09:30,200 --> 01:09:31,830
More than a few.

977
01:09:34,080 --> 01:09:35,580
We could leave.

978
01:09:36,080 --> 01:09:37,130
Tonight.

979
01:09:38,000 --> 01:09:42,050
Take my plane, go anywhere we wanted.

980
01:09:43,840 --> 01:09:45,630
Someday, perhaps.

981
01:09:46,590 --> 01:09:48,050
Not tonight.

982
01:10:16,250 --> 01:10:18,080
Don't be shy.

983
01:10:20,250 --> 01:10:22,670
Wayne says you can
get me the clean slate.

984
01:10:23,010 --> 01:10:25,760
- That depends.
- On what?

985
01:10:25,930 --> 01:10:27,550
On what you want it for.

986
01:10:27,720 --> 01:10:30,640
I acquired it to keep it
out of the wrong hands.

987
01:10:31,430 --> 01:10:33,180
Still don't trust me, huh?

988
01:10:34,310 --> 01:10:36,350
How can we change that?

989
01:10:36,520 --> 01:10:38,310
Start by taking me to Bane.

990
01:10:41,360 --> 01:10:42,940
You asked.

991
01:10:45,240 --> 01:10:47,280
From here, Bane's men
patrol the tunnels.

992
01:10:47,610 --> 01:10:50,070
And they're not your average brawlers.

993
01:10:50,570 --> 01:10:52,080
Neither am I.

994
01:10:59,880 --> 01:11:00,960
- He's behind you.
- Who?

995
01:11:01,130 --> 01:11:02,170
Me.

996
01:11:07,340 --> 01:11:09,300
What do you think you're...?

997
01:11:21,440 --> 01:11:23,650
Just a little further.

998
01:11:30,860 --> 01:11:33,410
I had to find a way to
stop them trying to kill me.

999
01:11:33,580 --> 01:11:35,990
You made a serious mistake.

1000
01:11:36,580 --> 01:11:41,500
Not as serious as yours, I fear.

1001
01:11:45,170 --> 01:11:46,210
Bane.

1002
01:11:46,380 --> 01:11:49,470
Let's not stand on ceremony here

1003
01:11:50,720 --> 01:11:53,050
Mr. Wayne.

1004
01:12:04,270 --> 01:12:06,440
Peace has cost you your strength.

1005
01:12:06,610 --> 01:12:08,440
Victory has defeated you.

1006
01:13:10,210 --> 01:13:15,840
Theatricality and deception,
powerful agents to the uninitiated.

1007
01:13:16,010 --> 01:13:18,810
But we are initiated, aren't we, Bruce?

1008
01:13:19,720 --> 01:13:22,560
Members of the League of Shadows.

1009
01:13:24,560 --> 01:13:26,940
And you betrayed us.

1010
01:13:27,770 --> 01:13:33,400
"Us"? You were excommunicated
by a gang of psychopaths.

1011
01:13:37,870 --> 01:13:40,790
I am the League of Shadows.

1012
01:13:40,950 --> 01:13:44,080
And I'm here to fulfill
Ra's Al Ghul's destiny.

1013
01:13:57,640 --> 01:13:59,720
You fight like a younger man.

1014
01:13:59,890 --> 01:14:02,180
Nothing held back.

1015
01:14:02,350 --> 01:14:05,560
Admirable, but mistaken.

1016
01:14:08,980 --> 01:14:13,570
Oh, you think darkness is your ally?

1017
01:14:13,740 --> 01:14:16,450
But you merely adopted the dark.

1018
01:14:17,110 --> 01:14:19,160
I was born in it.

1019
01:14:19,740 --> 01:14:21,870
Molded by it.

1020
01:14:23,040 --> 01:14:26,120
I didn't see the light
until I was already a man.

1021
01:14:26,290 --> 01:14:29,540
By then, it was nothing
to me but blinding!

1022
01:14:32,550 --> 01:14:36,510
The shadows betray you
because they belong to me!

1023
01:14:41,890 --> 01:14:45,100
I will show you where
I have made my home

1024
01:14:45,270 --> 01:14:48,600
whilst preparing to bring justice.

1025
01:14:50,810 --> 01:14:53,020
Then I will break you.

1026
01:15:01,780 --> 01:15:03,660
Your precious armory.

1027
01:15:04,330 --> 01:15:07,660
Gratefully accepted. We will need it.

1028
01:15:16,380 --> 01:15:20,180
Ah, yes. I was wondering
what would break first.

1029
01:15:24,930 --> 01:15:26,720
Your spirit

1030
