01:37:50,570 --> 01:37:53,190
so that I could, to my shame

1288
01:37:53,360 --> 01:37:59,870
build a lie around this fallen idol.

1289
01:38:02,160 --> 01:38:07,080
I praised the madman who
tried to murder my own child.

1290
01:38:07,290 --> 01:38:11,050
Well, I can no longer live with my lie.

1291
01:38:11,210 --> 01:38:14,970
It is time to trust the
people of Gotham with the truth

1292
01:38:15,130 --> 01:38:19,220
and it is time for me to resign."

1293
01:38:20,180 --> 01:38:23,520
And do you accept
this man's resignation?

1294
01:38:25,310 --> 01:38:29,520
And do you accept the
resignation of all of these liars?

1295
01:38:29,690 --> 01:38:31,360
Of all the corrupt?

1296
01:38:35,150 --> 01:38:37,410
Those men locked up for
eight years in Blackgate

1297
01:38:37,570 --> 01:38:41,830
and denied parole under the
Dent Act, it was based on a lie.

1298
01:38:42,870 --> 01:38:44,500
Gotham needed a hero.

1299
01:38:44,660 --> 01:38:46,640
Well, it needs it now more than ever,

1300
01:38:46,640 --> 01:38:48,880
but you betrayed
everything you stood for.

1301
01:38:50,790 --> 01:38:52,360
There's a point

1302
01:38:52,360 --> 01:38:56,470
far out there when
the structures fail you

1303
01:38:56,630 --> 01:38:59,510
when the rules aren't weapons anymore

1304
01:39:00,220 --> 01:39:03,680
they're shackles, letting
the bad guy get ahead.

1305
01:39:05,350 --> 01:39:10,610
One day, you may face
such a moment of crisis.

1306
01:39:10,770 --> 01:39:14,070
And in that moment, I hope
you have a friend like I did

1307
01:39:14,740 --> 01:39:17,570
to plunge their hands into the filth,

1308
01:39:17,570 --> 01:39:19,910
so that you can keep yours clean!

1309
01:39:21,450 --> 01:39:24,120
Your hands look plenty
filthy to me, commissioner.

1310
01:39:25,750 --> 01:39:29,250
We take Gotham from the corrupt!

1311
01:39:31,540 --> 01:39:32,630
The rich!

1312
01:39:33,550 --> 01:39:35,510
The oppressors of generations

1313
01:39:35,670 --> 01:39:39,840
who have kept you down
with myths of opportunity.

1314
01:39:40,010 --> 01:39:43,050
And we give it back to you

1315
01:39:43,680 --> 01:39:45,890
the people.

1316
01:39:46,980 --> 01:39:48,890
Gotham is yours!

1317
01:39:49,350 --> 01:39:52,690
None shall interfere. Do as you please.

1318
01:39:54,940 --> 01:39:58,440
But start by storming Blackgate
and freeing the oppressed!

1319
01:39:58,610 --> 01:40:00,320
Open it!

1320
01:40:08,250 --> 01:40:11,290
Step forward, those who would serve

1321
01:40:12,880 --> 01:40:14,630
for an army will be raised.

1322
01:40:18,880 --> 01:40:23,470
The powerful will be ripped
from their decadent nests

1323
01:40:28,180 --> 01:40:33,690
and cast out into the cold
world that we know and endure!

1324
01:40:38,280 --> 01:40:40,360
Courts will be convened.

1325
01:40:48,040 --> 01:40:50,330
Spoils will be enjoyed.

1326
01:40:55,130 --> 01:40:56,750
Blood will be shed!

1327
01:41:00,090 --> 01:41:02,760
The police will survive

1328
01:41:02,930 --> 01:41:07,350
as they learn to serve true justice.

1329
01:41:08,470 --> 01:41:10,980
This great city

1330
01:41:13,150 --> 01:41:14,650
it will endure.

1331
01:41:17,360 --> 01:41:21,110
Gotham will survive!

1332
01:41:42,930 --> 01:41:45,340
He says you must first fix your back.

1333
01:41:45,590 --> 01:41:46,720
How does he know?

1334
01:41:46,890 --> 01:41:48,300
He was the prison doctor.

1335
01:41:48,470 --> 01:41:54,040
He's a morphine addict who incurred
the displeasure of powerful people,

1336
01:41:54,040 --> 01:41:56,440
including your masked friend.

1337
01:41:57,360 --> 01:41:58,860
How?

1338
01:42:00,110 --> 01:42:04,400
Many years ago, it was a time of plague.

1339
01:42:05,990 --> 01:42:09,080
Some of the other
prisoners attacked Bane.

1340
01:42:11,120 --> 01:42:14,790
The doctor's fumbling
attempts to repair the damage

1341
01:42:15,580 --> 01:42:17,210
left him in perpetual agony.

1342
01:42:17,380 --> 01:42:20,550
The mask holds the pain at bay.

1343
01:42:20,710 --> 01:42:24,050
Bane was the child you spoke of?

1344
01:42:24,220 --> 01:42:25,510
He was born here?

1345
01:42:26,470 --> 01:42:28,940
The legend is that there was a mercenary

1346
01:42:28,940 --> 01:42:30,930
who worked for a local warlord.

1347
01:42:31,680 --> 01:42:34,020
He fell in love with
the warlord's daughter.

1348
01:42:34,520 --> 01:42:36,100
They were married in secret.

1349
01:42:36,270 --> 01:42:38,270
When the warlord found out

1350
01:42:38,770 --> 01:42:42,610
the mercenary was condemned to this pit.

1351
01:42:43,190 --> 01:42:45,440
But then he exiled him instead.

1352
01:42:45,610 --> 01:42:47,140
The mercenary understood that

1353
01:42:47,140 --> 01:42:49,660
it was the daughter who
had secured his release.

1354
01:42:49,830 --> 01:42:54,700
But what he could not know was
the true price of his freedom.

1355
01:42:55,750 --> 01:42:57,540
She took his place in the pit.

1356
01:43:00,670 --> 01:43:04,300
And she was with child,
the mercenary's child.

1357
01:43:06,880 --> 01:43:10,090
lnnocence cannot flower underground.
It has to be stamped out.

1358
01:43:12,720 --> 01:43:18,690
One day, the doctor
forgot to lock the cell.

1359
01:43:25,440 --> 01:43:30,300
But the child had a friend.
A protector who showed the

1360
01:43:30,300 --> 01:43:33,700
others that this innocence
was their redemption.

1361
01:43:33,870 --> 01:43:35,580
It was to be prized.

1362
01:43:35,750 --> 01:43:37,500
The mother was not so lucky.

1363
01:43:40,670 --> 01:43:44,340
This is Bane's prison now. He
wouldn't want this story told.

1364
01:43:55,720 --> 01:43:59,440
There's a vertebra
protruding from your back.

1365
01:43:59,810 --> 01:44:01,900
It has to be put back.

1366
01:44:06,900 --> 01:44:09,700
Stay like this until you stand.

1367
01:44:19,160 --> 01:44:22,630
Did you not think I
would return, Bruce? Hmm?

1368
01:44:28,300 --> 01:44:29,920
I told you I was immortal.

1369
01:44:32,470 --> 01:44:34,600
I watched... I watched you die.

1370
01:44:34,760 --> 01:44:37,720
Oh, there are many forms of immortality.

1371
01:44:39,640 --> 01:44:41,100
Once, I had a wife

1372
01:44:42,650 --> 01:44:44,360
my great love.

1373
01:44:45,730 --> 01:44:49,110
- She was taken from me.
- You were the mercenary.

1374
01:44:53,160 --> 01:44:55,120
Bane is your child.

1375
01:44:56,740 --> 01:44:57,790
Your heir.

1376
01:44:57,950 --> 01:45:01,340
An heir to ensure the League
of Shadows fulfills its duty

1377
01:45:01,340 --> 01:45:03,500
to restore balance to civilization.

1378
01:45:03,670 --> 01:45:04,710
No.

1379
01:45:04,880 --> 01:45:08,300
You yourself fought the
decadence of Gotham for years

1380
01:45:08,460 --> 01:45:12,490
with all your strength,
all your resources,

1381
01:45:12,500 --> 01:45:14,970
all your moral authority.

1382
01:45:15,720 --> 01:45:18,720
And the only victory you
could achieve was a lie.

1383
01:45:19,350 --> 01:45:22,230
Now you understand.
Gotham is beyond saving.

1384
01:45:22,390 --> 01:45:23,520
No.

1385
01:45:23,690 --> 01:45:25,810
- And must be allowed to die.
- No!

1386
01:45:32,740 --> 01:45:34,740
Yeah, just lift your head.

1387
01:45:35,160 --> 01:45:36,570
Oh, that's good.

1388
01:45:42,410 --> 01:45:43,460
No, no!

1389
01:46:18,830 --> 01:46:21,160
- What's that?
- This was someone's home.

1390
01:46:21,330 --> 01:46:23,250
And now it's everyone's home.

1391
01:46:25,040 --> 01:46:28,080
There's a storm coming,
remember? This is what you wanted.

1392
01:46:57,200 --> 01:46:59,990
It's for the bus, in case
there's a chance to evacuate.

1393
01:47:00,160 --> 01:47:01,700
Any news? Is the commissioner...?

1394
01:47:01,870 --> 01:47:05,200
The less you know, Father.
How are the boys doing?

1395
01:47:05,370 --> 01:47:08,170
Well, we've had more power
on, so they've got some TV.

1396
01:47:08,330 --> 01:47:09,670
It's good to see you.

1397
01:47:10,380 --> 01:47:12,280
Blake, you be careful out there.

1398
01:47:12,280 --> 01:47:14,420
They're hunting down cops like dogs.

1399
01:47:20,140 --> 01:47:21,430
Why build yourself?

1400
01:47:23,770 --> 01:47:25,980
I'm not meant to die in here.

1401
01:47:25,980 --> 01:47:28,730
Here, there. What's the difference?

1402
01:48:30,460 --> 01:48:33,790
I told you it could not be done.

1403
01:48:33,960 --> 01:48:35,590
You told me a child did it.

1404
01:48:36,960 --> 01:48:39,260
But no ordinary child.

1405
01:48:39,420 --> 01:48:42,220
A child born in hell.

1406
01:48:46,560 --> 01:48:48,020
Forged from suffering.

1407
01:48:50,140 --> 01:48:52,440
Hardened by pain.

1408
01:48:53,980 --> 01:48:56,610
Not a man from privilege.

1409
01:49:15,670 --> 01:49:17,630
We got boots on the ground, sir.

1410
01:49:18,420 --> 01:49:19,510
Just waiting on intel.

1411
01:49:25,220 --> 01:49:26,260
You have ID?

1412
01:49:26,970 --> 01:49:28,010
Of course not.

1413
01:49:28,180 --> 01:49:30,720
- Well, how can we trust you?
- We don't have any choice.

1414
01:49:31,600 --> 01:49:33,940
Commissioner Gordon. Captain
Jones, Special Forces.

1415
01:49:34,100 --> 01:49:35,650
Captain. Glad to have you here.

1416
01:49:35,810 --> 01:49:38,480
It's our job, sir. Now, uh,
how many of you are there?

1417
01:49:38,650 --> 01:49:41,570
Well, there's dozens. I'd
rather not say exactly.

1418
01:49:41,740 --> 01:49:44,990
But the men trapped
underground number almost 3000.

1419
01:49:45,160 --> 01:49:47,070
- Condition?
- Getting food and water.

1420
01:49:47,240 --> 01:49:49,540
- Can we break them out?
- Yes, sir.

1421
01:49:49,700 --> 01:49:52,040
Take out the mercenaries
south of Ackerman Park.

1422
01:49:52,210 --> 01:49:54,920
Blow the rubble, make a hole
big enough for 10 at a time.

1423
01:49:55,080 --> 01:49:57,270
I'm in contact with my
partner who's down there.

1424
01:49:57,270 --> 01:49:58,290
They're just waiting.

1425
01:49:58,460 --> 01:50:00,470
Men who haven't seen daylight in months?

1426
01:50:00,470 --> 01:50:02,720
Officers who haven't
seen daylight in months.

1427
01:50:02,880 --> 01:50:05,550
What about the bomb? Satellite
can't pick up radiation hot spots.

1428
01:50:06,090 --> 01:50:09,470
They keep it on a truck. It
must have a lead- lined roof.

1429
01:50:09,640 --> 01:50:12,310
- They move it constantly.
- Good. So you know the truck?

1430
01:50:12,480 --> 01:50:15,810
Well, it's one of three.
We've been tracking it.

1431
01:50:16,190 --> 01:50:17,230
Decoy.

1432
01:50:18,770 --> 01:50:20,780
You don't really think he's coming back?

1433
01:50:20,780 --> 01:50:22,190
Doesn't matter what I think.

1434
01:50:22,360 --> 01:50:23,290
Actually, it does.

1435
01:50:23,290 --> 01:50:26,240
You should put your faith in
something a little more real.

1436
01:50:26,410 --> 01:50:27,720
The routes don't vary much.

1437
01:50:27,720 --> 01:50:29,620
Okay. What about the triggerman?

1438
01:50:29,780 --> 01:50:30,970
No leads. It's a bluff.

1439
01:50:30,970 --> 01:50:33,830
Bane wouldn't give control
of that bomb to someone else.

1440
01:50:34,000 --> 01:50:35,350
We can't take that chance.

1441
01:50:35,350 --> 01:50:38,210
Until we have the triggerman,
we just track the device.

1442
01:50:38,380 --> 01:50:40,950
And meanwhile, Gotham
lives under a warlord,

1443
01:50:40,950 --> 01:50:42,300
like some failed state?

1444
01:50:42,460 --> 01:50:45,340
Dial it back, officer. This
situation is unprecedented.

1445
01:50:45,510 --> 01:50:48,280
We can't do anything to
risk millions of lives.

1446
01:50:48,280 --> 01:50:50,760
You gonna tell him
what's really going on?

1447
01:50:50,930 --> 01:50:54,020
Captain, the situation is more
complicated than you think.

1448
01:50:54,180 --> 01:50:56,390
There's someone you need to meet.

1449
01:50:56,730 --> 01:50:58,690
Came upstairs looking
for a vantage point.

1450
01:50:58,690 --> 01:51:00,610
Found the people who
run the corporation.

1451
01:51:00,770 --> 01:51:01,940
What corporation?

1452
01:51:02,110 --> 01:51:04,490
Wayne Enterprises. You good?

1453
01:51:13,540 --> 01:51:15,700
Mr. Fox, would you like
to brief the captain?

1454
01:51:15,910 --> 01:51:18,500
Miss Tate's fully
aware of the situation.

1455
01:51:18,670 --> 01:51:20,740
And as CEO of Wayne Enterprises,

1456
01:51:20,740 --> 01:51:23,130
I have to take responsibility for it.

1457
01:51:23,300 --> 01:51:25,300
- Why?
- We built it.

1458
01:51:25,470 --> 01:51:26,970
You built the bomb?

1459
01:51:27,130 --> 01:51:31,300
It was built as a fusion
reactor. First of its kind.

1460
01:51:31,470 --> 01:51:34,850
Bane turned the core into a bomb
and removed it from the reactor.

1461
01:51:35,020 --> 01:51:36,340
Here's the important part.

1462
01:51:36,340 --> 01:51:38,390
As the device's fuel cells deteriorate

1463
01:51:38,560 --> 01:51:42,190
it becomes increasingly unstable
to the point of detonation.

1464
01:51:42,360 --> 01:51:44,110
This bomb is a time bomb.

1465
01:51:44,280 --> 01:51:48,880
And it will go off in 23 days, regardless
of Bane's revolution or what we,

1466
01:51:48,880 --> 01:51:51,160
or the outside world, choose to do.

1467
01:51:51,320 --> 01:51:53,910
So your plan might not be
as practical as you thought.

1468
01:51:54,450 --> 01:51:55,940
Could you disarm it?

1469
01:51:55,940 --> 01:51:58,910
I could reconnect it to
the reactor. Stabilize it.

1470
01:51:59,080 --> 01:52:02,210
- Let's move from this location and call it in.
- Right. Let's go.

1471
01:52:02,380 --> 01:52:03,890
No, no, we'll take it from here.

1472
01:52:03,890 --> 01:52:05,590
You stay and look after these folks.

1473
01:52:12,930 --> 01:52:14,180
Someone sold us out.

1474
01:52:15,810 --> 01:52:17,270
Go, go, go!

1475
01:52:38,580 --> 01:52:40,660
I'll die before I talk.

1476
01:52:41,370 --> 01:52:43,630
I'm on your schedule, captain.

1477
01:52:50,090 --> 01:52:52,430
There were people living upstairs.

1478
01:52:52,930 --> 01:52:55,050
Round them up for judgment

1479
01:52:58,890 --> 01:53:03,770
and hang them where the world can see.

1480
01:53:18,500 --> 01:53:22,540
He says the leap to freedom
is not about strength.

1481
01:53:23,000 --> 01:53:24,960
My body makes the jump.

1482
01:53:25,460 --> 01:53:29,340
Survival is the spirit. The soul.

1483
01:53:32,260 --> 01:53:35,220
My soul is as ready
to escape as my body.

1484
01:53:35,390 --> 01:53:38,390
Fear is why you fail.

1485
01:53:38,680 --> 01:53:40,220
No, I'm not afraid.

1486
01:53:41,890 --> 01:53:43,390
I'm angry.

1487
01:54:12,630 --> 01:54:14,090
Bruce.

1488
01:54:15,300 --> 01:54:16,390
Why do we fall?

1489
01:54:22,430 --> 01:54:24,310
You do not fear death.

1490
01:54:25,350 --> 01:54:29,900
You think this makes you
strong. It makes you weak.

1491
01:54:30,440 --> 01:54:31,480
Why?

1492
01:54:31,650 --> 01:54:33,900
How can you move faster than possible

1493
01:54:34,200 --> 01:54:36,660
fight longer than possible

1494
01:54:36,950 --> 01:54:40,530
without the most powerful
impulse of the spirit?

1495
01:54:41,790 --> 01:54:43,410
The fear of death.

1496
01:54:44,120 --> 01:54:46,000
I do fear death.

1497
01:54:47,790 --> 01:54:49,750
I fear dying in here

1498
01:54:50,550 --> 01:54:52,460
while my city burns.

1499
01:54:53,510 --> 01:54:55,420
There's no one there to save it.

1500
01:54:56,800 --> 01:54:58,300
Then make the climb.

1501
01:55:03,350 --> 01:55:04,680
How?

1502
01:55:06,190 --> 01:55:07,980
As the child did

1503
01:55:12,690 --> 01:55:14,360
without the rope.

1504
01:55:17,030 --> 01:55:19,320
Then fear will find you again.

1505
01:55:26,330 --> 01:55:28,580
Ah, supplies for your journey?

1506
01:55:28,750 --> 01:55:32,310
Oh, that's wonderful.

1507
01:55:32,310 --> 01:55:37,010
That's What does that mean?

1508
01:55:37,550 --> 01:55:38,800
Rise.

1509
01:55:40,140 --> 01:55:41,180
No.

1510
01:57:11,140 --> 01:57:13,060
No, there's been a mistake!

1511
01:57:13,230 --> 01:57:15,230
Take me to Bane!

1512
01:57:17,820 --> 01:57:19,480
I want to see Bane!

1513
01:57:22,740 --> 01:57:23,820
Order!

1514
01:57:23,990 --> 01:57:26,740
This is a mistake! Where is Bane?

1515
01:57:26,910 --> 01:57:29,040
There's been no mistake, Mr. Stryver.

1516
01:57:29,410 --> 01:57:31,830
You are Philip Stryver

1517
01:57:32,000 --> 01:57:35,500
executive vice president
of Daggett lndustries

1518
01:57:35,670 --> 01:57:39,300
who for years has been
living off the blood and sweat

1519
01:57:39,460 --> 01:57:41,670
of people less powerful than him.

1520
01:57:41,840 --> 01:57:44,930
Call Bane. I am one of you.

1521
01:57:45,180 --> 01:57:48,720
Bane has no authority here. This
is merely a sentencing hearing.

1522
01:57:48,890 --> 01:57:51,020
Now, the choice is yours.

1523
01:57:51,180 --> 01:57:53,600
Exile or death!

1524
01:57:58,230 --> 01:57:59,650
Order!

1525
01:58:00,230 --> 01:58:01,530
Exi... Exile.

1526
01:58:02,280 --> 01:58:03,700
Sold.

1527
01:58:03,860 --> 01:58:05,610
To the man in the cold sweat.

1528
01:58:13,000 --> 01:58:14,410
You follow the thick ice.

1529
01:58:14,580 --> 01:58:16,710
You try to swim, you're dead in minutes.

1530
01:58:16,880 --> 01:58:18,460
Has anyone made it?

1531
01:58:31,890 --> 01:58:34,310
Where are they? It's not
like we have a lot of time.

1532
01:58:34,770 --> 01:58:35,890
How long?

1533
01:58:36,060 --> 01:58:37,900
The bomb goes off tomorrow.

1534
01:58:38,310 --> 01:58:40,890
We have about 18 hours to do something.

1535
01:58:40,890 --> 01:58:41,320
To do what?

1536
01:58:41,480 --> 01:58:43,090
To mark the truck. Get a GPS on it

1537
01:58:43,090 --> 01:58:45,490
so we can start to figure
out how to bring it down.

1538
01:58:52,200 --> 01:58:53,450
That's it?

1539
01:58:55,960 --> 01:58:57,040
Foley.

1540
01:58:58,580 --> 01:59:01,200
Where's Foley, damn it?

1541
01:59:01,200 --> 01:59:02,500
You shouldn't be out on the streets.

1542
01:59:07,220 --> 01:59:08,810
Jim, he's not here.

1543
01:59:08,810 --> 01:59:10,140
You let your wife come to the door?

1544
01:59:10,300 --> 01:59:13,350
- When the city's under occupation?
- Wait in the kitchen, honey.

1545
01:59:13,520 --> 01:59:16,140
What did you do, bury your
uniform in the backyard?

1546
01:59:16,310 --> 01:59:18,440
You saw what they did
to those Special Forces.

1547
01:59:18,600 --> 01:59:20,940
Have you forgotten all the
years we were out on patrol?

1548
01:59:21,110 --> 01:59:22,290
When every gangbanger wanted

1549
01:59:22,290 --> 01:59:24,230
to plant one as soon as
our backs were turned?

1550
01:59:24,400 --> 01:59:25,690
That was different. And you know it.

1551
01:59:25,700 --> 01:59:26,590
These guys run the city.

1552
01:59:26,590 --> 01:59:28,530
The government's done a deal with them.

1553
01:59:28,700 --> 01:59:31,240
Bane's got their balls in
a vice. That's not a deal.

1554
01:59:31,410 --> 01:59:34,700
You move on Bane, the triggerman
is gonna hit the button.

1555
01:59:34,870 --> 01:59:38,830
You think he's given control of
that bomb to one of the people?

1556
01:59:39,000 --> 01:59:41,000
You think this is part
of some revolution?

1557
01:59:41,170 --> 01:59:44,000
There's one man with his finger
on the button. That's Bane.

1558
01:59:44,170 --> 01:59:47,260
Look, we've all got to keep our
heads down till they can fix this.

1559
01:59:47,430 --> 01:59:49,290
If you still had a family here...

1560
01:59:49,290 --> 01:59:52,800
This only gets fixed
from inside the city!

1561
01:59:53,140 --> 01:59:54,140
Look, Peter.

1562
01:59:54,140 --> 01:59:58,770
I'm not asking you to walk
down Grand in your dress blues,

1563
01:59:58,770 --> 02:00:00,350
but something has to be done.

1564
02:00:00,520 --> 02:00:02,010
Sorry, Jim. I gotta...

1565
02:00:02,010 --> 02:00:02,560
Keep your head down?

1566
02:00:02,730 --> 02:00:04,900
What good's that gonna
do when that thing blows?

1567
02:00:05,070 --> 02:00:07,530
You don't know that's gonna happen.

1568
02:00:11,700 --> 02:00:13,990
I hear you're looking
for men, commissioner.

1569
02:00:14,160 --> 02:00:15,410
How about me instead?

1570
02:00:15,580 --> 02:00:18,160
Miss Tate, I, uh, can't
ask you to do that.

1571
02:00:19,120 --> 02:00:20,170
Please.

1572
02:00:21,750 --> 02:00:23,920
You little punk! What'd you take?

1573
02:00:24,090 --> 02:00:26,380
Nothing! I didn't take anything!

1574
02:00:26,550 --> 02:00:29,840
You steal from us, you little bastard?

1575
02:00:30,430 --> 02:00:31,860
Now, you boys know you can't

1576
02:00:31,860 --> 02:00:34,430
come into my neighborhood
without asking politely.

1577
02:00:40,350 --> 02:00:43,610
Never steal anything from
someone you can't outrun, kid.

1578
02:00:50,280 --> 02:00:52,320
You're pretty generous for a thief.

1579
02:01:01,000 --> 02:01:03,750
- I thought they killed you.
- Not yet.

1580
02:01:04,090 --> 02:01:06,050
If you're expecting an apology, I...

1581
02:01:06,050 --> 02:01:07,250
It wouldn't suit you.

1582
02:01:08,670 --> 02:01:09,710
I need your help.

1583
02:01:10,260 --> 02:01:11,720
And why would I help you?

1584
02:01:11,880 --> 02:01:13,890
For this. Clean slate.

1585
02:01:14,050 --> 02:01:16,050
You'd trust me with that?

1586
02:01:16,640 --> 02:01:18,270
After what I did to you?

1587
02:01:18,430 --> 02:01:21,350
I'll admit, I was a little let down.

1588
02:01:22,980 --> 02:01:24,680
But I still think there's more to you.

1589
02:01:24,680 --> 02:01:26,110
In fact, I think that for you

1590
02:01:26,520 --> 02:01:27,860
this isn't just a tool.

1591
02:01:28,030 --> 02:01:31,240
It's an escape route. You
want to disappear. Start fresh.

1592
02:01:32,150 --> 02:01:33,960
I can't even get off this island.

1593
02:01:33,960 --> 02:01:35,080
I can give you a way off

1594
02:01:35,080 --> 02:01:36,830
once you get me to Lucius Fox.

1595
02:01:36,990 --> 02:01:39,790
Find out where they're
holding him and take me in.

1596
02:01:43,540 --> 02:01:44,620
Why do you need Fox?

1597
02:01:44,790 --> 02:01:47,290
- To save the city.
- Who says it needs saving?

1598
02:01:47,460 --> 02:01:49,050
Maybe I like it this way.

1599
02:01:49,210 --> 02:01:50,840
Maybe you do

1600
02:01:52,220 --> 02:01:54,550
but tomorrow that bomb's going off.

1601
02:01:57,140 --> 02:01:58,850
Got your powerful friend on the case?

1602
02:01:59,020 --> 02:02:00,350
I'm trying

1603
02:02:01,180 --> 02:02:02,810
but I need Fox.

1604
02:02:02,980 --> 02:02:04,730
As it approaches

1605
02:02:05,520 --> 02:02:06,690
flip the switch.

1606
02:02:06,860 --> 02:02:09,080
The needle hits 200,
you give me the signal,

1607
02:02:09,080 --> 02:02:10,400
I'll mark the truck. Okay?

1608
02:02:11,780 --> 02:02:13,400
Heads up, heads up.

1609
02:02:29,500 --> 02:02:31,800
- I got it.
- Mercenaries on your 6.

1610
02:02:31,960 --> 02:02:35,090
Stand still! Keep your
hands where we can see them!

1611
02:02:37,300 --> 02:02:39,350
Commissioner Gordon,
you are under arrest.

1612
02:02:39,510 --> 02:02:41,220
On whose authority?

1613
02:02:41,390 --> 02:02:42,600
The people of Gotham.

1614
02:02:43,600 --> 02:02:46,170
No lawyer? No witnesses?

1615
02:02:46,170 --> 02:02:48,520
What sort of due process is this?

1616
02:02:48,690 --> 02:02:50,170
Your guilt has been determined,

1617
02:02:50,180 --> 02:02:51,900
this is merely a sentencing hearing.

1618
02:02:52,320 --> 02:02:53,900
Now, what will it be?

1619
02:02:55,110 --> 02:02:57,820
Death or exile?

1620
02:02:57,990 --> 02:02:59,180
Crane,

1621
02:02:59,180 --> 02:03:02,740
if you think we're going
out onto that ice willingly

1622
02:03:02,910 --> 02:03:04,500
you have another thing coming.

1623
02:03:07,000 --> 02:03:08,330
Death, then.

1624
02:03:08,500 --> 02:03:10,710
- Looks that way.
- Very well.

1625
02:03:10,880 --> 02:03:12,380
Death

1626
02:03:13,710 --> 02:03:15,420
by exile.

1627
02:03:18,010 --> 02:03:19,470
Bring her to me.

1628
02:03:25,980 --> 02:03:30,190
Hey, we're going now. Blake says
they're ready! Get your gear on!

1629
02:03:30,360 --> 02:03:33,400
Hey, you hear me? We're
going now. Let's do it.

1630
02:03:37,530 --> 02:03:39,780
Find this one a spot,
got a big day tomorrow.

1631
02:03:39,950 --> 02:03:40,810
We all do.

1632
02:03:40,810 --> 02:03:43,120
It's not every day you bag Bruce Wayne.

1633
02:03:45,370 --> 02:03:46,750
- Bruce.
- You okay?

1634
02:03:46,910 --> 02:03:49,290
Picked a hell of a time to
go on vacation, Mr. Wayne.

1635
02:03:49,460 --> 02:03:51,130
How long until that core ignites?

1636
02:03:51,290 --> 02:03:52,930
That bomb goes off in 12 hours.

1637
02:03:52,930 --> 02:03:55,130
- Unless we can reconnect
it to the reactor.

1638
02:03:55,880 --> 02:03:57,820
Can you get Miranda out of here?

1639
02:03:57,820 --> 02:03:59,010
Not tonight. I'm sorry.

1640
02:03:59,800 --> 02:04:02,050
- Do what's necessary.
- Tonight I need you.

1641
02:04:02,220 --> 02:04:04,640
- What for?
- To get me back in the game.

1642
02:04:04,810 --> 02:04:06,600
Sorry to spoil things, boys,

1643
02:04:06,600 --> 02:04:08,980
but Bane wants these guys to himself.

1644
02:04:11,310 --> 02:04:14,400
- I won't forget about you, Miranda.
- I know.

1645
02:04:23,700 --> 02:04:25,490
I like your girlfriend, Mr. Wayne.

1646
02:04:25,660 --> 02:04:27,500
He should be so lucky.

1647
02:04:33,250 --> 02:04:36,000
Any move I make on Bane or the bomb

1648
02:04:36,170 --> 02:04:38,050
the triggerman sets it off.

1649
02:04:38,220 --> 02:04:41,010
Well, they won't use radio or
cell. Too much interference.

1650
02:04:41,180 --> 02:04:42,840
lnfrared doesn't have the range.

1651
02:04:43,010 --> 02:04:45,760
It'll have to be a microburst. Longwave.

1652
02:04:45,930 --> 02:04:47,720
- Could you block it?
- Yes.

1653
02:04:47,890 --> 02:04:51,520
But I'll need the EMP cannon
guidance mount from the Bat.

1654
02:04:52,690 --> 02:04:54,310
Remember where you parked?

1655
02:05:08,700 --> 02:05:10,160
She fly okay?

1656
02:05:11,210 --> 02:05:13,920
Yeah, even without the autopilot.

1657
02:05:14,080 --> 02:05:14,930
Thanks.

1658
02:05:14,930 --> 02:05:17,050
Autopilot? That's what you're there for.

1659
02:05:56,790 --> 02:05:59,590
Okay. It's clear. Come
on, quick. One at a time.

1660
02:06:03,510 --> 02:06:04,840
Wait, wait!

1661
02:06:06,180 --> 02:06:07,640
Ross!

1662
02:06:07,810 --> 02:06:09,180
Ross?

1663
02:06:09,810 --> 02:06:11,890
Lock it up.

1664
02:06:12,560 --> 02:06:14,140
Get down!

1665
02:06:15,770 --> 02:06:17,020
Who are you?

1666
02:06:46,430 --> 02:06:47,720
Light it up.

1667
02:07:05,700 --> 02:07:08,870
- Dad, check it out.
- Honey, come take a look.

1668
02:07:19,250 --> 02:07:20,960
Impossible.

1669
02:07:21,750 --> 02:07:23,500
Keep her close.

1670
02:07:24,170 --> 02:07:25,840
He'll come for her.

1671
02:07:26,180 --> 02:07:27,930
Where's Miranda Tate?

1672
02:07:28,590 --> 02:07:30,050
Bane took her.

1673
02:07:30,260 --> 02:07:33,560
He's holed up at city hall,
surrounded by his army.

1674
02:07:33,850 --> 02:07:36,350
This blocks the remote
detonator signal to the bomb.

1675
02:07:36,520 --> 02:07:38,070
Get it onto it before sunrise.

1676
02:07:38,070 --> 02:07:40,190
They might hit the
button when it starts.

1677
02:07:41,110 --> 02:07:42,270
When what starts?

1678
02:07:42,780 --> 02:07:43,980
War.

1679
02:08:19,850 --> 02:08:20,980
You missed a spot.

1680
02:08:24,570 --> 02:08:26,750
If you're working alone, wear a mask.

1681
02:08:26,750 --> 02:08:29,450
I'm not afraid to be
seen standing up to them.

1682
02:08:29,610 --> 02:08:30,780
The mask is not for you.

1683
02:08:30,780 --> 02:08:32,820
It's to protect the
people you care about.

1684
02:08:34,540 --> 02:08:36,490
Count to five, then throw.

1685
02:08:46,880 --> 02:08:49,550
No offense, but you got
something bigger in that belt?

1686
02:08:59,980 --> 02:09:03,100
- What now? - All- out
assault on Bane.

1687
02:09:03,270 --> 02:09:05,520
But you need to get
people across the bridge.

1688
02:09:05,690 --> 02:09:06,380
Why?

1689
02:09:06,380 --> 02:09:07,940
In case we fail.

1690
02:09:08,110 --> 02:09:10,820
Lead an exodus. Save as
many lives as you can.

1691
02:09:10,990 --> 02:09:12,280
You don't need me here?

1692
02:09:12,450 --> 02:09:13,990
You've given me an army.

1693
02:09:14,160 --> 02:09:15,320
Now go.

1694
02:09:16,080 --> 02:09:17,160
Hey, thanks.

1695
02:09:17,330 --> 02:09:18,660
Don't thank me yet.

1696
02:09:18,830 --> 02:09:20,870
Well, I might not get a chance later.

1697
02:09:34,720 --> 02:09:36,430
You shouldn't have.

1698
02:09:37,390 --> 02:09:39,560
The midtown tunnel's blocked by debris

1699
02:09:39,730 --> 02:09:43,100
but the cannons have enough
firepower to make a path for people.

1700
02:09:43,270 --> 02:09:45,100
Wait until the fighting begins.

1701
02:09:45,270 --> 02:09:47,980
You're gonna wage a war to
save your stuck- up girlfriend?

1702
02:09:48,150 --> 02:09:49,190
To start it, throttle

1703
02:09:50,990 --> 02:09:51,760
I got it.

1704
02:09:51,760 --> 02:09:54,160
We have 45 minutes to save this city.

1705
02:09:54,320 --> 02:09:57,070
No, I've got 45 minutes to
get clear of the blast radius.

1706
02:09:57,240 --> 02:09:59,360
You don't stand a chance
against these guys.

1707
02:09:59,360 --> 02:10:00,540
With your help, I might.

1708
02:10:00,700 --> 02:10:03,080
I'll open that tunnel, then I'm gone.

1709
02:10:04,170 --> 02:10:05,750
There's more to you than that.

1710
02:10:09,420 --> 02:10:11,510
Sorry to keep letting you down.

1711
02:10:15,180 --> 02:10:19,600
Come with me. Save yourself.

1712
02:10:21,850 --> 02:10:24,560
You don't owe these people any more.

1713
02:10:24,730 --> 02:10:26,850
You've given them everything.

1714
02:10:27,020 --> 02:10:28,480
Not everything.

1715
02:10:28,900 --> 02:10:30,150
Not yet.

1716
02:11:10,190 --> 02:11:11,860
Disperse!

1717
02:11:12,030 --> 02:11:14,240
Disperse or be fired upon!

1718
02:11:15,650 --> 02:11:18,030
There's only one police in this town.

1719
02:11:57,030 --> 02:11:58,700
Open fire.

1720
02:12:49,920 --> 02:12:51,620
- Here it comes!
- Get ready!

1721
02:13:21,490 --> 02:13:25,570
So you came back to die with your city.

1722
02:13:25,910 --> 02:13:29,700
No. I came back to stop you.

1723
02:13:40,760 --> 02:13:41,800
Now!

1724
02:13:54,730 --> 02:13:56,360
That's impossible.

1725
02:13:58,230 --> 02:13:59,860
Cut over to Fifth!

1726
02:14:13,920 --> 02:14:15,920
Here you go. Get on the bus. Go ahead.

1727
02:14:16,080 --> 02:14:18,670
You, come with me. You too.

1728
02:14:18,880 --> 02:14:21,920
Hey, you, you, and you,
come here, come here.

1729
02:14:22,090 --> 02:14:23,920
Everyone else get on the bus, okay?

1730
02:14:24,090 --> 02:14:26,760
You guys, you go knock on
doors and spread the word, okay?

1731
02:14:26,930 --> 02:14:28,160
The bomb is gonna go off.

1732
02:14:28,160 --> 02:14:30,810
Get out by the South Street
tunnel or over the bridge.

1733
02:14:30,970 --> 02:14:33,680
You do two blocks and you get
back to the bus, all right?

1734
02:14:33,850 --> 02:14:35,730
Go, go, go!

1735
02:14:35,900 --> 02:14:37,270
Is he back?

1736
02:14:38,650 --> 02:14:39,980
Keep your eyes open. Go, go.

1737
02:16:02,610 --> 02:16:04,150
Cover the doors!

1738
02:16:07,320 --> 02:16:08,860
Where's your trigger?!

1739
02:16:09,200 --> 02:16:10,820
Where is it?!

1740
02:16:11,740 --> 02:16:14,580
You'd never give it
to an ordinary citizen!

1741
02:16:14,740 --> 02:16:17,370
Where is it? Where's your trigger?

1742
02:16:18,750 --> 02:16:21,460
Where is it?! Where is it?!

1743
02:16:29,260 --> 02:16:31,390
Tell me where the trigger is.

1744
02:16:31,890 --> 02:16:35,470
Then you have my permission to die.

1745
02:16:47,610 --> 02:16:49,320
I broke you.

1746
02:16:50,610 --> 02:16:52,490
How have you come back?

1747
02:16:52,660 --> 02:16:54,310
You think you're the only

1748
02:16:54,310 --> 02:16:57,160
one who could learn
the strength to escape?

1749
02:16:57,330 --> 02:16:58,620
Where's the trigger?

1750
02:16:59,290 --> 02:17:01,620
But I never escaped.

1751
02:17:02,500 --> 02:17:04,040
But the child.

1752
02:17:05,840 --> 02:17:07,880
The child of Ra's Al
Ghul made the climb.

1753
02:17:08,050 --> 02:17:10,420
But he's not the child of Ra's Al Ghul.

1754
02:17:14,350 --> 02:17:15,680
I am.

1755
02:17:16,140 --> 02:17:18,560
And though I'm not ordinary

1756
02:17:19,890 --> 02:17:21,600
I am a citizen.

1757
02:17:41,210 --> 02:17:42,370
Miranda?

1758
02:17:45,250 --> 02:17:46,290
Why?

1759
02:17:47,050 --> 02:17:48,380
Thalia.

1760
02:17:49,210 --> 02:17:52,260
My mother named me Talia,
before she was killed

1761
02:17:53,090 --> 02:17:58,010
the way I would have been killed,
if not for my protector, Bane.

1762
02:18:05,980 --> 02:18:07,150
Goodbye.

1763
02:18:09,400 --> 02:18:11,530
I climbed out of the pit.

1764
02:18:17,490 --> 02:18:19,290
I found my father

1765
02:18:22,250 --> 02:18:25,370
and brought him back to
exact terrible vengeance.

1766
02:18:26,250 --> 02:18:28,000
But by that time

1767
02:18:29,130 --> 02:18:32,880
the prisoners and doctor had
done their work to my friend.

1768
02:18:33,050 --> 02:18:34,260
My protector.

1769
02:18:38,260 --> 02:18:41,680
The League took us in. Trained us.

1770
02:18:42,060 --> 02:18:44,850
But my father could not accept Bane.

1771
02:18:45,400 --> 02:18:48,670
He saw only a monster.
His very existence

1772
02:18:48,670 --> 02:18:53,190
was a reminder of the hell
he'd left his wife to die in.

1773
02:18:53,610 --> 02:18:56,740
He excommunicated Bane
from the League of Shadows.

1774
02:18:56,910 --> 02:19:01,450
His only crime was that he loved me.

1775
02:19:03,250 --> 02:19:06,170
I could not forgive my father.

1776
02:19:10,800 --> 02:19:12,460
Until you murdered him.

1777
02:19:30,320 --> 02:19:35,780
He was trying to kill
millions of innocent people.

1778
02:19:36,070 --> 02:19:39,700
Innocent is a strong word to
throw around Gotham, Bruce.

1779
02:19:42,330 --> 02:19:45,370
I honor my father by finishing his work.

1780
02:19:57,550 --> 02:20:00,110
Vengeance against the man who killed him

1781
02:20:00,120 --> 02:20:02,430
is simply a reward for my patience.

1782
02:20:03,930 --> 02:20:05,020
You see

1783
02:20:06,560 --> 02:20:10,690
it's the slow knife the
knife that takes its time.

1784
02:20:14,480 --> 02:20:20,110
The knife that waits
years without forgetting

1785
02:20:20,410 --> 02:20:23,700
then slips quietly between the bones.

1786
02:20:24,740 --> 02:20:28,710
That's the knife that cuts deepest.

1787
02:20:28,870 --> 02:20:30,000
Please.

1788
02:20:37,720 --> 02:20:42,140
Maybe your knife was too slow.

1789
02:20:42,300 --> 02:20:43,720
The truck is under attack.

1790
02:20:43,890 --> 02:20:47,640
Gordon. You gave him a
way to block my signal.

1791
02:20:47,810 --> 02:20:48,850
No matter.

1792
02:20:51,400 --> 02:20:53,480
He's bought Gotham 11 minutes.

1793
02:20:57,860 --> 02:20:59,360
Come on!

1794
02:20:59,990 --> 02:21:01,410
This way!

1795
02:21:07,000 --> 02:21:09,410
Stay there! What are you doing?

1796
02:21:09,870 --> 02:21:10,760
Blake, MCU!

1797
02:21:10,760 --> 02:21:13,210
I'm getting these boys to safety!

1798
02:21:13,380 --> 02:21:14,710
You'll get us all killed!

1799
02:21:14,880 --> 02:21:16,630
If anyone crosses this bridge,

1800
02:21:16,630 --> 02:21:17,880
they'll blow the city!

1801
02:21:18,050 --> 02:21:21,430
It's gonna blow anyway! We
need to open this bridge, now!

1802
02:21:21,590 --> 02:21:24,760
Detective, if you take one
step forward we will shoot you!

1803
02:21:24,930 --> 02:21:28,520
If you take two steps forward,
we will blow the bridge!

1804
02:21:30,600 --> 02:21:33,030
Okay, go back by the bus
and wait for me, all right?

1805
02:21:33,030 --> 02:21:33,900
Go back and wait.

1806
02:21:37,150 --> 02:21:38,320
Prepare a convoy.

1807
02:21:38,320 --> 02:21:41,110
We must secure the
bomb until it detonates.

1808
02:21:42,450 --> 02:21:46,160
Don't kill him, I want
him to feel the heat.

1809
02:21:46,910 --> 02:21:51,790
Feel the fire of 12
million souls you failed.

1810
02:21:57,710 --> 02:21:59,250
Goodbye, my friend.

1811
02:22:07,350 --> 02:22:08,720
Goodbye.

1812
02:22:09,270 --> 02:22:12,770
Keep moving forward!
Flank them at the stairs!

1813
02:22:20,990 --> 02:22:22,740
Shoot them.

1814
02:22:23,400 --> 02:22:24,860
Shoot them all.

1815
02:22:34,080 --> 02:22:37,710
We both know that I
have to kill you now.

1816
02:22:40,630 --> 02:22:42,840
You'll just have to imagine the fire.

1817
02:22:50,680 --> 02:22:52,720
About the whole no- guns thing

1818
02:22:53,690 --> 02:22:56,730
I'm not sure I feel as
strongly about it as you do.

1819
02:23:10,120 --> 02:23:11,740
Pull up.

1820
02:23:14,460 --> 02:23:15,870
Stay level.

1821
02:23:28,260 --> 02:23:31,560
We have to force that convoy east
to the entrance to the reactor.

1822
02:23:33,390 --> 02:23:36,390
I need you on the ground,
I'll be in the air. Go.

1823
02:23:36,640 --> 02:23:39,900
The situation has changed.
Your orders are out of date.

1824
02:23:40,610 --> 02:23:44,070
I'm a cop, like you, and
I'm walking out there.

1825
02:23:44,900 --> 02:23:46,990
Please do not shoot me!

1826
02:23:48,950 --> 02:23:50,070
Shoot at his feet.

1827
02:24:00,080 --> 02:24:02,420
Nothing like a little air superiority.

1828
02:24:02,590 --> 02:24:08,340
Detective! Please stop!
Please, detective! Stop!

1829
02:24:08,510 --> 02:24:13,930
Stop walking! Blow it! Do it!

1830
02:24:25,230 --> 02:24:27,610
You have to get that bomb
here. You've got 10 minutes.

1831
02:24:38,580 --> 02:24:40,870
They're pushing us to the
entrance of the reactor.

1832
02:24:41,040 --> 02:24:43,500
They're gonna try to reconnect the core.

1833
02:24:44,800 --> 02:24:46,340
You idiots!

1834
02:24:46,630 --> 02:24:50,340
You sons of bitches! You're killing us!

1835
02:24:50,510 --> 02:24:52,140
Yeah, follow your orders!

1836
02:24:52,510 --> 02:24:54,810
All right, boys. Get in
a circle. Bow your heads.

1837
02:24:57,730 --> 02:24:59,520
It's on my side.

1838
02:25:47,480 --> 02:25:50,010
Hey, Father! Let's get
everyone back on the bus, okay?

1839
02:25:50,010 --> 02:25:52,230
Go, go, go! Back on the bus!

1840
02:25:52,230 --> 02:25:53,950
There's nowhere to go.

1841
02:25:54,490 --> 02:25:55,530
On the bus!

1842
02:26:52,420 --> 02:26:54,550
You've got to turn the truck east!

1843
02:26:59,470 --> 02:27:01,220
Stay straight!

1844
02:27:32,960 --> 02:27:36,340
Give me a hand! We
can get a cable on it!

1845
02:27:43,100 --> 02:27:45,930
Fox showed me how to
override the reactor.

1846
02:27:49,690 --> 02:27:50,940
Oh, dear.

1847
02:27:54,650 --> 02:27:57,990
lncluding the emergency flood.

1848
02:28:14,380 --> 02:28:20,890
There's no way this
bomb will be stopped.

1849
02:28:22,100 --> 02:28:23,220
What are you doing?

1850
02:28:23,390 --> 02:28:24,620
Protection from the blast.

1851
02:28:24,620 --> 02:28:25,770
We're gonna be all right!

1852
02:28:25,930 --> 02:28:27,230
It's an atom bomb!

1853
02:28:27,390 --> 02:28:28,620
Think they need to hear that?

1854
02:28:28,630 --> 02:28:30,060
Let them die without hope? Come on!

1855
02:28:30,980 --> 02:28:32,650
Prepare yourselves.

1856
02:28:34,360 --> 02:28:39,320
My father's work is done.

1857
02:28:45,120 --> 02:28:48,040
- What are you doing?
- I can get it out over the bay!

1858
02:28:48,500 --> 02:28:50,710
Set it to fly out over
the water, then eject?

1859
02:28:50,880 --> 02:28:52,500
No autopilot.

1860
02:28:54,130 --> 02:28:55,530
You could've gone anywhere,

1861
02:28:55,530 --> 02:28:57,510
been anything. But you came back here.

1862
02:28:57,670 --> 02:28:58,800
So did you.

1863
02:28:59,260 --> 02:29:01,300
I guess we're both suckers.

1864
02:29:08,980 --> 02:29:11,810
- I never cared who you were.
- And you were right.

1865
02:29:11,980 --> 02:29:14,560
Shouldn't the people know
the hero who saved them?

1866
02:29:14,730 --> 02:29:15,900
A hero can be anyone.

1867
02:29:16,070 --> 02:29:19,520
Even a man doing something
as simple and reassuring as

1868
02:29:19,520 --> 02:29:22,480
putting a coat around
a young boy's shoulders

1869
02:29:22,480 --> 02:29:24,990
to let him know the world hadn't ended.

1870
02:29:42,720 --> 02:29:44,180
Bruce Wayne?

1871
02:29:57,270 --> 02:29:59,480
Come on! There you go! Okay, you too.

1872
02:29:59,480 --> 02:30:00,400
Come on, Father.

1873
02:30:19,670 --> 02:30:21,550
Hey, heads down! This is it!

1874
02:30:21,880 --> 02:30:24,800
- No.
- No, that's Batman!

1875
02:31:13,020 --> 02:31:14,310
That's detonation!

1876
02:31:21,780 --> 02:31:23,690
It's out over the
bay! Clear of the city!

1877
02:31:43,550 --> 02:31:46,380
"I see a beautiful city

1878
02:31:46,550 --> 02:31:50,930
and a brilliant people
rising from this abyss.

1879
02:31:52,140 --> 02:31:56,140
I see the lives for
which I lay down my life

1880
02:31:56,560 --> 02:32:01,770
peaceful useful, prosperous and happy.

1881
02:32:04,240 --> 02:32:07,860
I see that I hold a
sanctuary in their hearts

1882
02:32:09,700 --> 02:32:12,870
and in the hearts of their descendants

1883
02:32:13,700 --> 02:32:15,410
generations hence.

1884
02:32:18,120 --> 02:32:22,340
It is a far, far better thing that I do

1885
02:32:23,210 --> 02:32:25,170
than I have ever done.

1886
02:32:26,220 --> 02:32:30,720
It is a far, far
better rest that I go to

1887
02:32:33,640 --> 02:32:35,350
than I have ever known."

1888
02:32:53,700 --> 02:32:55,120
I'm so sorry.

1889
02:32:55,490 --> 02:32:57,200
I failed you.

1890
02:32:59,250 --> 02:33:00,870
You trusted me

1891
02:33:02,460 --> 02:33:03,590
and I failed you.

1892
02:33:07,720 --> 02:33:09,510
Can I change your mind

1893
02:33:11,840 --> 02:33:13,760
about quitting the force?

1894
02:33:14,680 --> 02:33:18,520
You know what you said about
structures becoming shackles?

1895
02:33:18,890 --> 02:33:22,440
You were right, and I can't
take it. The injustice.

1896
02:33:22,650 --> 02:33:26,940
I mean, no one's ever gonna
know who saved an entire city.

1897
02:33:27,150 --> 02:33:28,230
They know.

1898
02:33:30,150 --> 02:33:31,860
It was the Batman.

1899
02:33:49,920 --> 02:33:51,640
Mr. Wayne's will was not amended

1900
02:33:51,640 --> 02:33:53,510
to reflect his more modest estate.

1901
02:33:53,680 --> 02:33:57,510
Nonetheless, there are
considerable assets to dispose of.

1902
02:33:57,680 --> 02:33:59,600
The contents of the house are to be sold

1903
02:33:59,600 --> 02:34:01,140
to settle the estate's accounts

1904
02:34:01,310 --> 02:34:02,970
and the remainder is left

1905
02:34:02,970 --> 02:34:05,650
in its entirety to Alfred J. Pennyworth.

1906
02:34:07,110 --> 02:34:10,670
The house and grounds are
left to the city of Gotham

1907
02:34:10,680 --> 02:34:13,970
on condition that they
never be demolished, altered

1908
02:34:13,970 --> 02:34:15,870
or otherwise interfered with

1909
02:34:16,030 --> 02:34:19,830
and that they shall be used for
one purpose, and one purpose only:

1910
02:34:21,500 --> 02:34:25,750
The housing and care of the city's
at- risk and orphaned children.

1911
02:34:26,340 --> 02:34:27,800
My clerk can help with

1912
02:34:27,800 --> 02:34:30,800
the smaller correspondences
and instructions.

1913
02:34:30,970 --> 02:34:32,380
Blake, John.

1914
02:34:32,680 --> 02:34:35,930
- Nothing here.
- Uh, try my legal name.

1915
02:34:39,350 --> 02:34:42,140
You should use your full
name. I like that name.

1916
02:34:42,310 --> 02:34:44,190
- Robin.
- Thanks.

1917
02:34:44,350 --> 02:34:46,520
Why worry about the
stabilization software?

1918
02:34:46,690 --> 02:34:48,690
This entire autopilot
system's completely obsolete.

1919
02:34:48,860 --> 02:34:52,650
Please, I just need to know
what I could've done to fix it.

1920
02:34:52,820 --> 02:34:53,620
But, Mr. Fox,

1921
02:34:53,620 --> 02:34:56,060
it's already been fixed. Software patch.

1922
02:34:56,060 --> 02:34:56,950
Six months ago.

1923
02:34:57,120 --> 02:34:58,700
Check the ID on the patch.

1924
02:35:01,790 --> 02:35:03,370
Bruce Wayne.

1925
02:35:04,250 --> 02:35:06,540
- Any news on the missing item?
- Not yet.

1926
02:35:06,710 --> 02:35:08,130
They better leave no stone unturned.

1927
02:35:08,290 --> 02:35:11,710
We can't leave a string of
pearls on the manifest as lost.

